113struct ImBitVector; // Store 1-bit per value
114struct ImRect; // An axis-aligned rectangle (2 points)
115struct ImDrawDataBuilder; // Helper to build a ImDrawData instance
116struct ImDrawListSharedData; // Data shared between all ImDrawList instances
117struct ImGuiColorMod; // Stacked color modifier, backup of modified data so we can restore it
118struct ImGuiContext; // Main Dear ImGui context
119struct ImGuiContextHook; // Hook for extensions like ImGuiTestEngine
120struct ImGuiDataTypeInfo; // Type information associated to a ImGuiDataType enum
121struct ImGuiDockContext; // Docking system context
122struct ImGuiDockRequest; // Docking system dock/undock queued request
123struct ImGuiDockNode; // Docking system node (hold a list of Windows OR two child dock nodes)
124struct ImGuiDockNodeSettings; // Storage for a dock node in .ini file (we preserve those even if the associated dock node isn't active during the session)
125struct ImGuiGroupData; // Stacked storage data for BeginGroup()/EndGroup()
126struct ImGuiInputTextState; // Internal state of the currently focused/edited text input box
127struct ImGuiLastItemData; // Status storage for last submitted items
128struct ImGuiMenuColumns; // Simple column measurement, currently used for MenuItem() only
129struct ImGuiNavItemData; // Result of a gamepad/keyboard directional navigation move query result
130struct ImGuiMetricsConfig; // Storage for ShowMetricsWindow() and DebugNodeXXX() functions
131struct ImGuiNextWindowData; // Storage for SetNextWindow** functions
132struct ImGuiNextItemData; // Storage for SetNextItem** functions
133struct ImGuiOldColumnData; // Storage data for a single column for legacy Columns() api
134struct ImGuiOldColumns; // Storage data for a columns set for legacy Columns() api
135struct ImGuiPopupData; // Storage for current popup stack
136struct ImGuiSettingsHandler; // Storage for one type registered in the .ini file
137struct ImGuiStackSizes; // Storage of stack sizes for debugging/asserting
138struct ImGuiStyleMod; // Stacked style modifier, backup of modified data so we can restore it
139struct ImGuiTabBar; // Storage for a tab bar
140struct ImGuiTabItem; // Storage for a tab item (within a tab bar)
141struct ImGuiTable; // Storage for a table
142struct ImGuiTableColumn; // Storage for one column of a table
143struct ImGuiTableInstanceData; // Storage for one instance of a same table
144struct ImGuiTableTempData; // Temporary storage for one table (one per table in the stack), shared between tables.
145struct ImGuiTableSettings; // Storage for a table .ini settings
146struct ImGuiTableColumnsSettings; // Storage for a column .ini settings
147struct ImGuiWindow; // Storage for one window
148struct ImGuiWindowTempData; // Temporary storage for one window (that's the data which in theory we could ditch at the end of the frame, in practice we currently keep it for each window)
149struct ImGuiWindowSettings; // Storage for a window .ini settings (we keep one of those even if the actual window wasn't instanced during this session)

205// Debug Printing Into TTY
206// (since IMGUI_VERSION_NUM >= 18729: IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG was reworked into IMGUI_DEBUG_PRINTF (and removed framecount from it). If you were using a #define IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG please rename)
207#ifndef IMGUI_DEBUG_PRINTF
208#ifndef IMGUI_DISABLE_DEFAULT_FORMAT_FUNCTIONS

211#define IMGUI_DEBUG_PRINTF(_FMT,...)

215// Debug Logging for ShowDebugLogWindow(). This is designed for relatively rare events so please don't spam.
216#define IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG(...) ImGui::DebugLog(__VA_ARGS__);
217#define IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG_ACTIVEID(...) do { if (g.DebugLogFlags & ImGuiDebugLogFlags_EventActiveId) IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG(__VA_ARGS__); } while (0)
218#define IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG_FOCUS(...) do { if (g.DebugLogFlags & ImGuiDebugLogFlags_EventFocus) IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG(__VA_ARGS__); } while (0)
219#define IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG_POPUP(...) do { if (g.DebugLogFlags & ImGuiDebugLogFlags_EventPopup) IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG(__VA_ARGS__); } while (0)
220#define IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG_NAV(...) do { if (g.DebugLogFlags & ImGuiDebugLogFlags_EventNav) IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG(__VA_ARGS__); } while (0)
221#define IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG_IO(...) do { if (g.DebugLogFlags & ImGuiDebugLogFlags_EventIO) IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG(__VA_ARGS__); } while (0)
222#define IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG_DOCKING(...) do { if (g.DebugLogFlags & ImGuiDebugLogFlags_EventDocking) IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG(__VA_ARGS__); } while (0)
223#define IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG_VIEWPORT(...) do { if (g.DebugLogFlags & ImGuiDebugLogFlags_EventViewport) IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG(__VA_ARGS__); } while (0)

225// Static Asserts
226#define IM_STATIC_ASSERT(_COND) static_assert(_COND, "")
227
228// "Paranoid" Debug Asserts are meant to only be enabled during specific debugging/work, otherwise would slow down the code too much.
229// We currently don't have many of those so the effect is currently negligible, but onward intent to add more aggressive ones in the code.
230//#define IMGUI_DEBUG_PARANOID
231#ifdef IMGUI_DEBUG_PARANOID
232#define IM_ASSERT_PARANOID(_EXPR) IM_ASSERT(_EXPR)
233#else
234#define IM_ASSERT_PARANOID(_EXPR)
235#endif

237// Error handling
238// Down the line in some frameworks/languages we would like to have a way to redirect those to the programmer and recover from more faults.
239#ifndef IM_ASSERT_USER_ERROR
240#define IM_ASSERT_USER_ERROR(_EXP,_MSG) IM_ASSERT((_EXP) && _MSG) // Recoverable User Error
241#endif

245#ifdef _WIN32
246#define IM_NEWLINE "\r\n" // Play it nice with Windows users (Update: since 2018-05, Notepad finally appears to support Unix-style carriage returns!)
247#else
248#define IM_NEWLINE "\n"
249#endif
250#define IM_TABSIZE (4)
251#define IM_MEMALIGN(_OFF,_ALIGN) (((_OFF) + ((_ALIGN) - 1)) & ~((_ALIGN) - 1)) // Memory align e.g. IM_ALIGN(0,4)=0, IM_ALIGN(1,4)=4, IM_ALIGN(4,4)=4, IM_ALIGN(5,4)=8
252#define IM_F32_TO_INT8_UNBOUND(_VAL) ((int)((_VAL) * 255.0f + ((_VAL)>=0 ? 0.5f : -0.5f))) // Unsaturated, for display purpose
253#define IM_F32_TO_INT8_SAT(_VAL) ((int)(ImSaturate(_VAL) * 255.0f + 0.5f)) // Saturated, always output 0..255
254#define IM_FLOOR(_VAL) ((float)(int)(_VAL)) // ImFloor() is not inlined in MSVC debug builds
255#define IM_ROUND(_VAL) ((float)(int)((_VAL) + 0.5f)) //

271// Debug Tools
272// Use 'Metrics/Debugger->Tools->Item Picker' to break into the call-stack of a specific item.
273// This will call IM_DEBUG_BREAK() which you may redefine yourself. See https://github.com/scottt/debugbreak for more reference.
274#ifndef IM_DEBUG_BREAK
275#if defined (_MSC_VER)
276#define IM_DEBUG_BREAK() __debugbreak()
277#elif defined(__clang__)
278#define IM_DEBUG_BREAK() __builtin_debugtrap()
279#elif defined(__GNUC__) && (defined(__i386__) || defined(__x86_64__))
280#define IM_DEBUG_BREAK() __asm__ volatile("int $0x03")
281#elif defined(__GNUC__) && defined(__thumb__)
282#define IM_DEBUG_BREAK() __asm__ volatile(".inst 0xde01")
283#elif defined(__GNUC__) && defined(__arm__) && !defined(__thumb__)
284#define IM_DEBUG_BREAK() __asm__ volatile(".inst 0xe7f001f0");
285#else
286#define IM_DEBUG_BREAK() IM_ASSERT(0) // It is expected that you define IM_DEBUG_BREAK() into something that will break nicely in a debugger!
287#endif
288#endif // #ifndef IM_DEBUG_BREAK

318// Helpers: Sorting
319#ifndef ImQsort
320static inline void ImQsort(void* base, size_t count, size_t size_of_element, int(IMGUI_CDECL *compare_func)(void const*, void const*)) { if (count > 1) qsort(base, count, size_of_element, compare_func); }
321#endif

323// Helpers: Color Blending
324IMGUI_API ImU32 ImAlphaBlendColors(ImU32 col_a, ImU32 col_b);
325
326// Helpers: Bit manipulation
327static inline bool ImIsPowerOfTwo(int v) { return v != 0 && (v & (v - 1)) == 0; }
328static inline bool ImIsPowerOfTwo(ImU64 v) { return v != 0 && (v & (v - 1)) == 0; }
329static inline int ImUpperPowerOfTwo(int v) { v--; v |= v >> 1; v |= v >> 2; v |= v >> 4; v |= v >> 8; v |= v >> 16; v++; return v; }

368// Helpers: ImVec2/ImVec4 operators
369// We are keeping those disabled by default so they don't leak in user space, to allow user enabling implicit cast operators between ImVec2 and their own types (using IM_VEC2_CLASS_EXTRA etc.)
370// We unfortunately don't have a unary- operator for ImVec2 because this would needs to be defined inside the class itself.
371#ifdef IMGUI_DEFINE_MATH_OPERATORS
372IM_MSVC_RUNTIME_CHECKS_OFF
373static inline ImVec2 operator*(const ImVec2& lhs, const float rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x * rhs, lhs.y * rhs); }
374static inline ImVec2 operator/(const ImVec2& lhs, const float rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x / rhs, lhs.y / rhs); }
375static inline ImVec2 operator+(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x + rhs.x, lhs.y + rhs.y); }
376static inline ImVec2 operator-(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x - rhs.x, lhs.y - rhs.y); }
377static inline ImVec2 operator*(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x * rhs.x, lhs.y * rhs.y); }
378static inline ImVec2 operator/(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x / rhs.x, lhs.y / rhs.y); }
379static inline ImVec2& operator*=(ImVec2& lhs, const float rhs) { lhs.x *= rhs; lhs.y *= rhs; return lhs; }
380static inline ImVec2& operator/=(ImVec2& lhs, const float rhs) { lhs.x /= rhs; lhs.y /= rhs; return lhs; }
381static inline ImVec2& operator+=(ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { lhs.x += rhs.x; lhs.y += rhs.y; return lhs; }
382static inline ImVec2& operator-=(ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { lhs.x -= rhs.x; lhs.y -= rhs.y; return lhs; }
383static inline ImVec2& operator*=(ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { lhs.x *= rhs.x; lhs.y *= rhs.y; return lhs; }
384static inline ImVec2& operator/=(ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { lhs.x /= rhs.x; lhs.y /= rhs.y; return lhs; }
385static inline ImVec4 operator+(const ImVec4& lhs, const ImVec4& rhs) { return ImVec4(lhs.x + rhs.x, lhs.y + rhs.y, lhs.z + rhs.z, lhs.w + rhs.w); }
386static inline ImVec4 operator-(const ImVec4& lhs, const ImVec4& rhs) { return ImVec4(lhs.x - rhs.x, lhs.y - rhs.y, lhs.z - rhs.z, lhs.w - rhs.w); }
387static inline ImVec4 operator*(const ImVec4& lhs, const ImVec4& rhs) { return ImVec4(lhs.x * rhs.x, lhs.y * rhs.y, lhs.z * rhs.z, lhs.w * rhs.w); }
388IM_MSVC_RUNTIME_CHECKS_RESTORE
389#endif

413// Helpers: Maths
414IM_MSVC_RUNTIME_CHECKS_OFF
415// - Wrapper for standard libs functions. (Note that imgui_demo.cpp does _not_ use them to keep the code easy to copy)
416#ifndef IMGUI_DISABLE_DEFAULT_MATH_FUNCTIONS
417#define ImFabs(X) fabsf(X)
418#define ImSqrt(X) sqrtf(X)
419#define ImFmod(X, Y) fmodf((X), (Y))
420#define ImCos(X) cosf(X)
421#define ImSin(X) sinf(X)
422#define ImAcos(X) acosf(X)
423#define ImAtan2(Y, X) atan2f((Y), (X))
424#define ImAtof(STR) atof(STR)
425//#define ImFloorStd(X) floorf(X) // We use our own, see ImFloor() and ImFloorSigned()
426#define ImCeil(X) ceilf(X)
427static inline float ImPow(float x, float y) { return powf(x, y); } // DragBehaviorT/SliderBehaviorT uses ImPow with either float/double and need the precision
428static inline double ImPow(double x, double y) { return pow(x, y); }
429static inline float ImLog(float x) { return logf(x); } // DragBehaviorT/SliderBehaviorT uses ImLog with either float/double and need the precision
430static inline double ImLog(double x) { return log(x); }
431static inline int ImAbs(int x) { return x < 0 ? -x : x; }
432static inline float ImAbs(float x) { return fabsf(x); }
433static inline double ImAbs(double x) { return fabs(x); }
434static inline float ImSign(float x) { return (x < 0.0f) ? -1.0f : (x > 0.0f) ? 1.0f : 0.0f; } // Sign operator - returns -1, 0 or 1 based on sign of argument
435static inline double ImSign(double x) { return (x < 0.0) ? -1.0 : (x > 0.0) ? 1.0 : 0.0; }
436#ifdef IMGUI_ENABLE_SSE
437static inline float ImRsqrt(float x) { return _mm_cvtss_f32(_mm_rsqrt_ss(_mm_set_ss(x))); }
438#else
439static inline float ImRsqrt(float x) { return 1.0f / sqrtf(x); }
440#endif
441static inline double ImRsqrt(double x) { return 1.0 / sqrt(x); }
442#endif
443// - ImMin/ImMax/ImClamp/ImLerp/ImSwap are used by widgets which support variety of types: signed/unsigned int/long long float/double
444// (Exceptionally using templates here but we could also redefine them for those types)
445template<typename T> static inline T ImMin(T lhs, T rhs) { return lhs < rhs ? lhs : rhs; }
446template<typename T> static inline T ImMax(T lhs, T rhs) { return lhs >= rhs ? lhs : rhs; }
447template<typename T> static inline T ImClamp(T v, T mn, T mx) { return (v < mn) ? mn : (v > mx) ? mx : v; }
448template<typename T> static inline T ImLerp(T a, T b, float t) { return (T)(a + (b - a) * t); }
449template<typename T> static inline void ImSwap(T& a, T& b) { T tmp = a; a = b; b = tmp; }
450template<typename T> static inline T ImAddClampOverflow(T a, T b, T mn, T mx) { if (b < 0 && (a < mn - b)) return mn; if (b > 0 && (a > mx - b)) return mx; return a + b; }
451template<typename T> static inline T ImSubClampOverflow(T a, T b, T mn, T mx) { if (b > 0 && (a < mn + b)) return mn; if (b < 0 && (a > mx + b)) return mx; return a - b; }
452// - Misc maths helpers
453static inline ImVec2 ImMin(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x < rhs.x ? lhs.x : rhs.x, lhs.y < rhs.y ? lhs.y : rhs.y); }
454static inline ImVec2 ImMax(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x >= rhs.x ? lhs.x : rhs.x, lhs.y >= rhs.y ? lhs.y : rhs.y); }
455static inline ImVec2 ImClamp(const ImVec2& v, const ImVec2& mn, ImVec2 mx) { return ImVec2((v.x < mn.x) ? mn.x : (v.x > mx.x) ? mx.x : v.x, (v.y < mn.y) ? mn.y : (v.y > mx.y) ? mx.y : v.y); }
456static inline ImVec2 ImLerp(const ImVec2& a, const ImVec2& b, float t) { return ImVec2(a.x + (b.x - a.x) * t, a.y + (b.y - a.y) * t); }
457static inline ImVec2 ImLerp(const ImVec2& a, const ImVec2& b, const ImVec2& t) { return ImVec2(a.x + (b.x - a.x) * t.x, a.y + (b.y - a.y) * t.y); }
458static inline ImVec4 ImLerp(const ImVec4& a, const ImVec4& b, float t) { return ImVec4(a.x + (b.x - a.x) * t, a.y + (b.y - a.y) * t, a.z + (b.z - a.z) * t, a.w + (b.w - a.w) * t); }
459static inline float ImSaturate(float f) { return (f < 0.0f) ? 0.0f : (f > 1.0f) ? 1.0f : f; }
460static inline float ImLengthSqr(const ImVec2& lhs) { return (lhs.x * lhs.x) + (lhs.y * lhs.y); }
461static inline float ImLengthSqr(const ImVec4& lhs) { return (lhs.x * lhs.x) + (lhs.y * lhs.y) + (lhs.z * lhs.z) + (lhs.w * lhs.w); }
462static inline float ImInvLength(const ImVec2& lhs, float fail_value) { float d = (lhs.x * lhs.x) + (lhs.y * lhs.y); if (d > 0.0f) return ImRsqrt(d); return fail_value; }
463static inline float ImFloor(float f) { return (float)(int)(f); }
464static inline float ImFloorSigned(float f) { return (float)((f >= 0 || (float)(int)f == f) ? (int)f : (int)f - 1); } // Decent replacement for floorf()
465static inline ImVec2 ImFloor(const ImVec2& v) { return ImVec2((float)(int)(v.x), (float)(int)(v.y)); }
466static inline ImVec2 ImFloorSigned(const ImVec2& v) { return ImVec2(ImFloorSigned(v.x), ImFloorSigned(v.y)); }
467static inline int ImModPositive(int a, int b) { return (a + b) % b; }
468static inline float ImDot(const ImVec2& a, const ImVec2& b) { return a.x * b.x + a.y * b.y; }
469static inline ImVec2 ImRotate(const ImVec2& v, float cos_a, float sin_a) { return ImVec2(v.x * cos_a - v.y * sin_a, v.x * sin_a + v.y * cos_a); }
470static inline float ImLinearSweep(float current, float target, float speed) { if (current < target) return ImMin(current + speed, target); if (current > target) return ImMax(current - speed, target); return current; }
471static inline ImVec2 ImMul(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x * rhs.x, lhs.y * rhs.y); }
472static inline bool ImIsFloatAboveGuaranteedIntegerPrecision(float f) { return f <= -16777216 || f >= 16777216; }

506// Helper: ImRect (2D axis aligned bounding-box)
507// NB: we can't rely on ImVec2 math operators being available here!
508struct IMGUI_API ImRect
509{
510 ImVec2 Min; // Upper-left
511 ImVec2 Max; // Lower-right
512
513 constexpr ImRect() : Min(0.0f, 0.0f), Max(0.0f, 0.0f) {}
514 constexpr ImRect(const ImVec2& min, const ImVec2& max) : Min(min), Max(max) {}
515 constexpr ImRect(const ImVec4& v) : Min(v.x, v.y), Max(v.z, v.w) {}
516 constexpr ImRect(float x1, float y1, float x2, float y2) : Min(x1, y1), Max(x2, y2) {}
517
518 ImVec2 GetCenter() const { return ImVec2((Min.x + Max.x) * 0.5f, (Min.y + Max.y) * 0.5f); }
519 ImVec2 GetSize() const { return ImVec2(Max.x - Min.x, Max.y - Min.y); }
520 float GetWidth() const { return Max.x - Min.x; }
521 float GetHeight() const { return Max.y - Min.y; }
522 float GetArea() const { return (Max.x - Min.x) * (Max.y - Min.y); }
523 ImVec2 GetTL() const { return Min; } // Top-left
524 ImVec2 GetTR() const { return ImVec2(Max.x, Min.y); } // Top-right
525 ImVec2 GetBL() const { return ImVec2(Min.x, Max.y); } // Bottom-left
526 ImVec2 GetBR() const { return Max; } // Bottom-right
527 bool Contains(const ImVec2& p) const { return p.x >= Min.x && p.y >= Min.y && p.x < Max.x && p.y < Max.y; }
528 bool Contains(const ImRect& r) const { return r.Min.x >= Min.x && r.Min.y >= Min.y && r.Max.x <= Max.x && r.Max.y <= Max.y; }
529 bool Overlaps(const ImRect& r) const { return r.Min.y < Max.y && r.Max.y > Min.y && r.Min.x < Max.x && r.Max.x > Min.x; }
530 void Add(const ImVec2& p) { if (Min.x > p.x) Min.x = p.x; if (Min.y > p.y) Min.y = p.y; if (Max.x < p.x) Max.x = p.x; if (Max.y < p.y) Max.y = p.y; }
531 void Add(const ImRect& r) { if (Min.x > r.Min.x) Min.x = r.Min.x; if (Min.y > r.Min.y) Min.y = r.Min.y; if (Max.x < r.Max.x) Max.x = r.Max.x; if (Max.y < r.Max.y) Max.y = r.Max.y; }
532 void Expand(const float amount) { Min.x -= amount; Min.y -= amount; Max.x += amount; Max.y += amount; }
533 void Expand(const ImVec2& amount) { Min.x -= amount.x; Min.y -= amount.y; Max.x += amount.x; Max.y += amount.y; }
534 void Translate(const ImVec2& d) { Min.x += d.x; Min.y += d.y; Max.x += d.x; Max.y += d.y; }
535 void TranslateX(float dx) { Min.x += dx; Max.x += dx; }
536 void TranslateY(float dy) { Min.y += dy; Max.y += dy; }
537 void ClipWith(const ImRect& r) { Min = ImMax(Min, r.Min); Max = ImMin(Max, r.Max); } // Simple version, may lead to an inverted rectangle, which is fine for Contains/Overlaps test but not for display.
538 void ClipWithFull(const ImRect& r) { Min = ImClamp(Min, r.Min, r.Max); Max = ImClamp(Max, r.Min, r.Max); } // Full version, ensure both points are fully clipped.
539 void Floor() { Min.x = IM_FLOOR(Min.x); Min.y = IM_FLOOR(Min.y); Max.x = IM_FLOOR(Max.x); Max.y = IM_FLOOR(Max.y); }
540 bool IsInverted() const { return Min.x > Max.x || Min.y > Max.y; }
541 ImVec4 ToVec4() const { return ImVec4(Min.x, Min.y, Max.x, Max.y); }
542};
543IM_MSVC_RUNTIME_CHECKS_RESTORE

545// Helper: ImBitArray
546inline bool ImBitArrayTestBit(const ImU32* arr, int n) { ImU32 mask = (ImU32)1 << (n & 31); return (arr[n >> 5] & mask) != 0; }
547inline void ImBitArrayClearBit(ImU32* arr, int n) { ImU32 mask = (ImU32)1 << (n & 31); arr[n >> 5] &= ~mask; }
548inline void ImBitArraySetBit(ImU32* arr, int n) { ImU32 mask = (ImU32)1 << (n & 31); arr[n >> 5] |= mask; }
549inline void ImBitArraySetBitRange(ImU32* arr, int n, int n2) // Works on range [n..n2)
550{
551 n2--;
552 while (n <= n2)
553 {
554 int a_mod = (n & 31);
555 int b_mod = (n2 > (n | 31) ? 31 : (n2 & 31)) + 1;
556 ImU32 mask = (ImU32)(((ImU64)1 << b_mod) - 1) & ~(ImU32)(((ImU64)1 << a_mod) - 1);
557 arr[n >> 5] |= mask;
558 n = (n + 32) & ~31;
559 }
560}
561
562// Helper: ImBitArray class (wrapper over ImBitArray functions)
563// Store 1-bit per value.
564template<int BITCOUNT, int OFFSET = 0>
565struct ImBitArray
566{
567 ImU32 Storage[(BITCOUNT + 31) >> 5];
568 ImBitArray() { ClearAllBits(); }
569 void ClearAllBits() { memset(Storage, 0, sizeof(Storage)); }
570 void SetAllBits() { memset(Storage, 255, sizeof(Storage)); }
571 bool TestBit(int n) const { n += OFFSET; IM_ASSERT(n >= 0 && n < BITCOUNT); return ImBitArrayTestBit(Storage, n); }
572 void SetBit(int n) { n += OFFSET; IM_ASSERT(n >= 0 && n < BITCOUNT); ImBitArraySetBit(Storage, n); }
573 void ClearBit(int n) { n += OFFSET; IM_ASSERT(n >= 0 && n < BITCOUNT); ImBitArrayClearBit(Storage, n); }
574 void SetBitRange(int n, int n2) { n += OFFSET; n2 += OFFSET; IM_ASSERT(n >= 0 && n < BITCOUNT && n2 > n && n2 <= BITCOUNT); ImBitArraySetBitRange(Storage, n, n2); } // Works on range [n..n2)
575 bool operator[](int n) const { n += OFFSET; IM_ASSERT(n >= 0 && n < BITCOUNT); return ImBitArrayTestBit(Storage, n); }
576};
577
578// Helper: ImBitVector
579// Store 1-bit per value.
580struct IMGUI_API ImBitVector
581{
582 ImVector<ImU32> Storage;
583 void Create(int sz) { Storage.resize((sz + 31) >> 5); memset(Storage.Data, 0, (size_t)Storage.Size * sizeof(Storage.Data[0])); }
584 void Clear() { Storage.clear(); }
585 bool TestBit(int n) const { IM_ASSERT(n < (Storage.Size << 5)); return ImBitArrayTestBit(Storage.Data, n); }
586 void SetBit(int n) { IM_ASSERT(n < (Storage.Size << 5)); ImBitArraySetBit(Storage.Data, n); }
587 void ClearBit(int n) { IM_ASSERT(n < (Storage.Size << 5)); ImBitArrayClearBit(Storage.Data, n); }
588};
589
590// Helper: ImSpan<>
591// Pointing to a span of data we don't own.
592template<typename T>
593struct ImSpan
594{
595 T* Data;
596 T* DataEnd;
597
598 // Constructors, destructor
599 inline ImSpan() { Data = DataEnd = NULL; }
600 inline ImSpan(T* data, int size) { Data = data; DataEnd = data + size; }
601 inline ImSpan(T* data, T* data_end) { Data = data; DataEnd = data_end; }
602
603 inline void set(T* data, int size) { Data = data; DataEnd = data + size; }
604 inline void set(T* data, T* data_end) { Data = data; DataEnd = data_end; }
605 inline int size() const { return (int)(ptrdiff_t)(DataEnd - Data); }
606 inline int size_in_bytes() const { return (int)(ptrdiff_t)(DataEnd - Data) * (int)sizeof(T); }
607 inline T& operator[](int i) { T* p = Data + i; IM_ASSERT(p >= Data && p < DataEnd); return *p; }
608 inline const T& operator[](int i) const { const T* p = Data + i; IM_ASSERT(p >= Data && p < DataEnd); return *p; }
609
610 inline T* begin() { return Data; }
611 inline const T* begin() const { return Data; }
612 inline T* end() { return DataEnd; }
613 inline const T* end() const { return DataEnd; }
614
615 // Utilities
616 inline int index_from_ptr(const T* it) const { IM_ASSERT(it >= Data && it < DataEnd); const ptrdiff_t off = it - Data; return (int)off; }
617};
618
619// Helper: ImSpanAllocator<>
620// Facilitate storing multiple chunks into a single large block (the "arena")
621// - Usage: call Reserve() N times, allocate GetArenaSizeInBytes() worth, pass it to SetArenaBasePtr(), call GetSpan() N times to retrieve the aligned ranges.
622template<int CHUNKS>
623struct ImSpanAllocator
624{
625 char* BasePtr;
626 int CurrOff;
627 int CurrIdx;
628 int Offsets[CHUNKS];
629 int Sizes[CHUNKS];
630
631 ImSpanAllocator() { memset(this, 0, sizeof(*this)); }
632 inline void Reserve(int n, size_t sz, int a=4) { IM_ASSERT(n == CurrIdx && n < CHUNKS); CurrOff = IM_MEMALIGN(CurrOff, a); Offsets[n] = CurrOff; Sizes[n] = (int)sz; CurrIdx++; CurrOff += (int)sz; }
633 inline int GetArenaSizeInBytes() { return CurrOff; }
634 inline void SetArenaBasePtr(void* base_ptr) { BasePtr = (char*)base_ptr; }
635 inline void* GetSpanPtrBegin(int n) { IM_ASSERT(n >= 0 && n < CHUNKS && CurrIdx == CHUNKS); return (void*)(BasePtr + Offsets[n]); }
636 inline void* GetSpanPtrEnd(int n) { IM_ASSERT(n >= 0 && n < CHUNKS && CurrIdx == CHUNKS); return (void*)(BasePtr + Offsets[n] + Sizes[n]); }
637 template<typename T>
638 inline void GetSpan(int n, ImSpan<T>* span) { span->set((T*)GetSpanPtrBegin(n), (T*)GetSpanPtrEnd(n)); }
639};
640
641// Helper: ImPool<>
642// Basic keyed storage for contiguous instances, slow/amortized insertion, O(1) indexable, O(Log N) queries by ID over a dense/hot buffer,
643// Honor constructor/destructor. Add/remove invalidate all pointers. Indexes have the same lifetime as the associated object.
644typedef int ImPoolIdx;
645template<typename T>
646struct ImPool
647{
648 ImVector<T> Buf; // Contiguous data
649 ImGuiStorage Map; // ID->Index
650 ImPoolIdx FreeIdx; // Next free idx to use
651 ImPoolIdx AliveCount; // Number of active/alive items (for display purpose)
652
653 ImPool() { FreeIdx = AliveCount = 0; }
654 ~ImPool() { Clear(); }
655 T* GetByKey(ImGuiID key) { int idx = Map.GetInt(key, -1); return (idx != -1) ? &Buf[idx] : NULL; }
656 T* GetByIndex(ImPoolIdx n) { return &Buf[n]; }
657 ImPoolIdx GetIndex(const T* p) const { IM_ASSERT(p >= Buf.Data && p < Buf.Data + Buf.Size); return (ImPoolIdx)(p - Buf.Data); }
658 T* GetOrAddByKey(ImGuiID key) { int* p_idx = Map.GetIntRef(key, -1); if (*p_idx != -1) return &Buf[*p_idx]; *p_idx = FreeIdx; return Add(); }
659 bool Contains(const T* p) const { return (p >= Buf.Data && p < Buf.Data + Buf.Size); }
660 void Clear() { for (int n = 0; n < Map.Data.Size; n++) { int idx = Map.Data[n].val_i; if (idx != -1) Buf[idx].~T(); } Map.Clear(); Buf.clear(); FreeIdx = AliveCount = 0; }
661 T* Add() { int idx = FreeIdx; if (idx == Buf.Size) { Buf.resize(Buf.Size + 1); FreeIdx++; } else { FreeIdx = *(int*)&Buf[idx]; } IM_PLACEMENT_NEW(&Buf[idx]) T(); AliveCount++; return &Buf[idx]; }
662 void Remove(ImGuiID key, const T* p) { Remove(key, GetIndex(p)); }
663 void Remove(ImGuiID key, ImPoolIdx idx) { Buf[idx].~T(); *(int*)&Buf[idx] = FreeIdx; FreeIdx = idx; Map.SetInt(key, -1); AliveCount--; }
664 void Reserve(int capacity) { Buf.reserve(capacity); Map.Data.reserve(capacity); }
665
666 // To iterate a ImPool: for (int n = 0; n < pool.GetMapSize(); n++) if (T* t = pool.TryGetMapData(n)) { ... }
667 // Can be avoided if you know .Remove() has never been called on the pool, or AliveCount == GetMapSize()
668 int GetAliveCount() const { return AliveCount; } // Number of active/alive items in the pool (for display purpose)
669 int GetBufSize() const { return Buf.Size; }
670 int GetMapSize() const { return Map.Data.Size; } // It is the map we need iterate to find valid items, since we don't have "alive" storage anywhere
671 T* TryGetMapData(ImPoolIdx n) { int idx = Map.Data[n].val_i; if (idx == -1) return NULL; return GetByIndex(idx); }
672#ifndef IMGUI_DISABLE_OBSOLETE_FUNCTIONS
673 int GetSize() { return GetMapSize(); } // For ImPlot: should use GetMapSize() from (IMGUI_VERSION_NUM >= 18304)
674#endif
675};
676
677// Helper: ImChunkStream<>
678// Build and iterate a contiguous stream of variable-sized structures.
679// This is used by Settings to store persistent data while reducing allocation count.
680// We store the chunk size first, and align the final size on 4 bytes boundaries.
681// The tedious/zealous amount of casting is to avoid -Wcast-align warnings.
682template<typename T>
683struct ImChunkStream
684{
685 ImVector<char> Buf;
686
687 void clear() { Buf.clear(); }
688 bool empty() const { return Buf.Size == 0; }
689 int size() const { return Buf.Size; }
690 T* alloc_chunk(size_t sz) { size_t HDR_SZ = 4; sz = IM_MEMALIGN(HDR_SZ + sz, 4u); int off = Buf.Size; Buf.resize(off + (int)sz); ((int*)(void*)(Buf.Data + off))[0] = (int)sz; return (T*)(void*)(Buf.Data + off + (int)HDR_SZ); }
691 T* begin() { size_t HDR_SZ = 4; if (!Buf.Data) return NULL; return (T*)(void*)(Buf.Data + HDR_SZ); }
692 T* next_chunk(T* p) { size_t HDR_SZ = 4; IM_ASSERT(p >= begin() && p < end()); p = (T*)(void*)((char*)(void*)p + chunk_size(p)); if (p == (T*)(void*)((char*)end() + HDR_SZ)) return (T*)0; IM_ASSERT(p < end()); return p; }
693 int chunk_size(const T* p) { return ((const int*)p)[-1]; }
694 T* end() { return (T*)(void*)(Buf.Data + Buf.Size); }
695 int offset_from_ptr(const T* p) { IM_ASSERT(p >= begin() && p < end()); const ptrdiff_t off = (const char*)p - Buf.Data; return (int)off; }
696 T* ptr_from_offset(int off) { IM_ASSERT(off >= 4 && off < Buf.Size); return (T*)(void*)(Buf.Data + off); }
697 void swap(ImChunkStream<T>& rhs) { rhs.Buf.swap(Buf); }
698
699};
700
701//-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
702// [SECTION] ImDrawList support
703//-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
704
705// ImDrawList: Helper function to calculate a circle's segment count given its radius and a "maximum error" value.
706// Estimation of number of circle segment based on error is derived using method described in https://stackoverflow.com/a/2244088/15194693
707// Number of segments (N) is calculated using equation:
708// N = ceil ( pi / acos(1 - error / r) ) where r > 0, error <= r
709// Our equation is significantly simpler that one in the post thanks for choosing segment that is
710// perpendicular to X axis. Follow steps in the article from this starting condition and you will
711// will get this result.
712//
713// Rendering circles with an odd number of segments, while mathematically correct will produce
714// asymmetrical results on the raster grid. Therefore we're rounding N to next even number (7->8, 8->8, 9->10 etc.)
715#define IM_ROUNDUP_TO_EVEN(_V) ((((_V) + 1) / 2) * 2)
716#define IM_DRAWLIST_CIRCLE_AUTO_SEGMENT_MIN 4
717#define IM_DRAWLIST_CIRCLE_AUTO_SEGMENT_MAX 512
718#define IM_DRAWLIST_CIRCLE_AUTO_SEGMENT_CALC(_RAD,_MAXERROR) ImClamp(IM_ROUNDUP_TO_EVEN((int)ImCeil(IM_PI / ImAcos(1 - ImMin((_MAXERROR), (_RAD)) / (_RAD)))), IM_DRAWLIST_CIRCLE_AUTO_SEGMENT_MIN, IM_DRAWLIST_CIRCLE_AUTO_SEGMENT_MAX)
719
720// Raw equation from IM_DRAWLIST_CIRCLE_AUTO_SEGMENT_CALC rewritten for 'r' and 'error'.
721#define IM_DRAWLIST_CIRCLE_AUTO_SEGMENT_CALC_R(_N,_MAXERROR) ((_MAXERROR) / (1 - ImCos(IM_PI / ImMax((float)(_N), IM_PI))))
722#define IM_DRAWLIST_CIRCLE_AUTO_SEGMENT_CALC_ERROR(_N,_RAD) ((1 - ImCos(IM_PI / ImMax((float)(_N), IM_PI))) / (_RAD))
723
724// ImDrawList: Lookup table size for adaptive arc drawing, cover full circle.
725#ifndef IM_DRAWLIST_ARCFAST_TABLE_SIZE
726#define IM_DRAWLIST_ARCFAST_TABLE_SIZE 48 // Number of samples in lookup table.
727#endif
728#define IM_DRAWLIST_ARCFAST_SAMPLE_MAX IM_DRAWLIST_ARCFAST_TABLE_SIZE // Sample index _PathArcToFastEx() for 360 angle.
729
730// Data shared between all ImDrawList instances
731// You may want to create your own instance of this if you want to use ImDrawList completely without ImGui. In that case, watch out for future changes to this structure.
732struct IMGUI_API ImDrawListSharedData
733{
734 ImVec2 TexUvWhitePixel; // UV of white pixel in the atlas
735 ImFont* Font; // Current/default font (optional, for simplified AddText overload)
736 float FontSize; // Current/default font size (optional, for simplified AddText overload)
737 float CurveTessellationTol; // Tessellation tolerance when using PathBezierCurveTo()
738 float CircleSegmentMaxError; // Number of circle segments to use per pixel of radius for AddCircle() etc
739 ImVec4 ClipRectFullscreen; // Value for PushClipRectFullscreen()
740 ImDrawListFlags InitialFlags; // Initial flags at the beginning of the frame (it is possible to alter flags on a per-drawlist basis afterwards)
741
742 // [Internal] Lookup tables
743 ImVec2 ArcFastVtx[IM_DRAWLIST_ARCFAST_TABLE_SIZE]; // Sample points on the quarter of the circle.
744 float ArcFastRadiusCutoff; // Cutoff radius after which arc drawing will fallback to slower PathArcTo()
745 ImU8 CircleSegmentCounts[64]; // Precomputed segment count for given radius before we calculate it dynamically (to avoid calculation overhead)
746 const ImVec4* TexUvLines; // UV of anti-aliased lines in the atlas
747
748 ImDrawListSharedData();
749 void SetCircleTessellationMaxError(float max_error);
750};
751
752struct ImDrawDataBuilder
753{
754 ImVector<ImDrawList*> Layers[2]; // Global layers for: regular, tooltip
755
756 void Clear() { for (int n = 0; n < IM_ARRAYSIZE(Layers); n++) Layers[n].resize(0); }
757 void ClearFreeMemory() { for (int n = 0; n < IM_ARRAYSIZE(Layers); n++) Layers[n].clear(); }
758 int GetDrawListCount() const { int count = 0; for (int n = 0; n < IM_ARRAYSIZE(Layers); n++) count += Layers[n].Size; return count; }
759 IMGUI_API void FlattenIntoSingleLayer();
760};

766// Transient per-window flags, reset at the beginning of the frame. For child window, inherited from parent on first Begin().
767// This is going to be exposed in imgui.h when stabilized enough.
768enum ImGuiItemFlags_
769{
770 // Controlled by user
771 ImGuiItemFlags_None = 0,
772 ImGuiItemFlags_NoTabStop = 1 << 0, // false // Disable keyboard tabbing (FIXME: should merge with _NoNav)
773 ImGuiItemFlags_ButtonRepeat = 1 << 1, // false // Button() will return true multiple times based on io.KeyRepeatDelay and io.KeyRepeatRate settings.
774 ImGuiItemFlags_Disabled = 1 << 2, // false // Disable interactions but doesn't affect visuals. See BeginDisabled()/EndDisabled(). See github.com/ocornut/imgui/issues/211
775 ImGuiItemFlags_NoNav = 1 << 3, // false // Disable keyboard/gamepad directional navigation (FIXME: should merge with _NoTabStop)
776 ImGuiItemFlags_NoNavDefaultFocus = 1 << 4, // false // Disable item being a candidate for default focus (e.g. used by title bar items)
777 ImGuiItemFlags_SelectableDontClosePopup = 1 << 5, // false // Disable MenuItem/Selectable() automatically closing their popup window
778 ImGuiItemFlags_MixedValue = 1 << 6, // false // [BETA] Represent a mixed/indeterminate value, generally multi-selection where values differ. Currently only supported by Checkbox() (later should support all sorts of widgets)
779 ImGuiItemFlags_ReadOnly = 1 << 7, // false // [ALPHA] Allow hovering interactions but underlying value is not changed.
780
781 // Controlled by widget code
782 ImGuiItemFlags_Inputable = 1 << 8 // false // [WIP] Auto-activate input mode when tab focused. Currently only used and supported by a few items before it becomes a generic feature.
783};

1017// Internal state of the currently focused/edited text input box
1018// For a given item ID, access with ImGui::GetInputTextState()
1019struct IMGUI_API ImGuiInputTextState
1020{
1021 ImGuiID ID; // widget id owning the text state
1022 int CurLenW, CurLenA; // we need to maintain our buffer length in both UTF-8 and wchar format. UTF-8 length is valid even if TextA is not.
1023 ImVector<ImWchar> TextW; // edit buffer, we need to persist but can't guarantee the persistence of the user-provided buffer. so we copy into own buffer.
1024 ImVector<char> TextA; // temporary UTF8 buffer for callbacks and other operations. this is not updated in every code-path! size=capacity.
1025 ImVector<char> InitialTextA; // backup of end-user buffer at the time of focus (in UTF-8, unaltered)
1026 bool TextAIsValid; // temporary UTF8 buffer is not initially valid before we make the widget active (until then we pull the data from user argument)
1027 int BufCapacityA; // end-user buffer capacity
1028 float ScrollX; // horizontal scrolling/offset
1029 ImStb::STB_TexteditState Stb; // state for stb_textedit.h
1030 float CursorAnim; // timer for cursor blink, reset on every user action so the cursor reappears immediately
1031 bool CursorFollow; // set when we want scrolling to follow the current cursor position (not always!)
1032 bool SelectedAllMouseLock; // after a double-click to select all, we ignore further mouse drags to update selection
1033 bool Edited; // edited this frame
1034 ImGuiInputTextFlags Flags; // copy of InputText() flags
1035
1036 ImGuiInputTextState() { memset(this, 0, sizeof(*this)); }
1037 void ClearText() { CurLenW = CurLenA = 0; TextW[0] = 0; TextA[0] = 0; CursorClamp(); }
1038 void ClearFreeMemory() { TextW.clear(); TextA.clear(); InitialTextA.clear(); }
1039 int GetUndoAvailCount() const { return Stb.undostate.undo_point; }
1040 int GetRedoAvailCount() const { return STB_TEXTEDIT_UNDOSTATECOUNT - Stb.undostate.redo_point; }
1041 void OnKeyPressed(int key); // Cannot be inline because we call in code in stb_textedit.h implementation
1042
1043 // Cursor & Selection
1044 void CursorAnimReset() { CursorAnim = -0.30f; } // After a user-input the cursor stays on for a while without blinking
1045 void CursorClamp() { Stb.cursor = ImMin(Stb.cursor, CurLenW); Stb.select_start = ImMin(Stb.select_start, CurLenW); Stb.select_end = ImMin(Stb.select_end, CurLenW); }
1046 bool HasSelection() const { return Stb.select_start != Stb.select_end; }
1047 void ClearSelection() { Stb.select_start = Stb.select_end = Stb.cursor; }
1048 int GetCursorPos() const { return Stb.cursor; }
1049 int GetSelectionStart() const { return Stb.select_start; }
1050 int GetSelectionEnd() const { return Stb.select_end; }
1051 void SelectAll() { Stb.select_start = 0; Stb.cursor = Stb.select_end = CurLenW; Stb.has_preferred_x = 0; }
1052};

1310 ImGuiScrollFlags_KeepVisibleEdgeY = 1 << 1, // If item is not visible: scroll as little as possible on Y axis to bring item back into view [default for Y axis for windows that are already visible]
1311 ImGuiScrollFlags_KeepVisibleCenterX = 1 << 2, // If item is not visible: scroll to make the item centered on X axis [rarely used]
1312 ImGuiScrollFlags_KeepVisibleCenterY = 1 << 3, // If item is not visible: scroll to make the item centered on Y axis
1313 ImGuiScrollFlags_AlwaysCenterX = 1 << 4, // Always center the result item on X axis [rarely used]
1314 ImGuiScrollFlags_AlwaysCenterY = 1 << 5, // Always center the result item on Y axis [default for Y axis for appearing window)
1315 ImGuiScrollFlags_NoScrollParent = 1 << 6, // Disable forwarding scrolling to parent window if required to keep item/rect visible (only scroll window the function was applied to).
1316 ImGuiScrollFlags_MaskX_ = ImGuiScrollFlags_KeepVisibleEdgeX | ImGuiScrollFlags_KeepVisibleCenterX | ImGuiScrollFlags_AlwaysCenterX,

1448// Extend ImGuiDockNodeFlags_
1449enum ImGuiDockNodeFlagsPrivate_
1450{
1451 // [Internal]
1452 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_DockSpace = 1 << 10, // Local, Saved // A dockspace is a node that occupy space within an existing user window. Otherwise the node is floating and create its own window.
1453 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_CentralNode = 1 << 11, // Local, Saved // The central node has 2 main properties: stay visible when empty, only use "remaining" spaces from its neighbor.
1454 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoTabBar = 1 << 12, // Local, Saved // Tab bar is completely unavailable. No triangle in the corner to enable it back.
1455 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_HiddenTabBar = 1 << 13, // Local, Saved // Tab bar is hidden, with a triangle in the corner to show it again (NB: actual tab-bar instance may be destroyed as this is only used for single-window tab bar)
1456 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoWindowMenuButton = 1 << 14, // Local, Saved // Disable window/docking menu (that one that appears instead of the collapse button)
1457 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoCloseButton = 1 << 15, // Local, Saved //
1458 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoDocking = 1 << 16, // Local, Saved // Disable any form of docking in this dockspace or individual node. (On a whole dockspace, this pretty much defeat the purpose of using a dockspace at all). Note: when turned on, existing docked nodes will be preserved.
1459 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoDockingSplitMe = 1 << 17, // [EXPERIMENTAL] Prevent another window/node from splitting this node.
1460 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoDockingSplitOther = 1 << 18, // [EXPERIMENTAL] Prevent this node from splitting another window/node.
1461 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoDockingOverMe = 1 << 19, // [EXPERIMENTAL] Prevent another window/node to be docked over this node.
1462 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoDockingOverOther = 1 << 20, // [EXPERIMENTAL] Prevent this node to be docked over another window or non-empty node.
1463 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoDockingOverEmpty = 1 << 21, // [EXPERIMENTAL] Prevent this node to be docked over an empty node (e.g. DockSpace with no other windows)
1464 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoResizeX = 1 << 22, // [EXPERIMENTAL]
1465 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoResizeY = 1 << 23, // [EXPERIMENTAL]
1466 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_SharedFlagsInheritMask_ = ~0,
1467 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoResizeFlagsMask_ = ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoResize | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoResizeX | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoResizeY,
1468 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_LocalFlagsMask_ = ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoSplit | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoResizeFlagsMask_ | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_AutoHideTabBar | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_DockSpace | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_CentralNode | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoTabBar | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_HiddenTabBar | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoWindowMenuButton | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoCloseButton | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoDocking,
1469 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_LocalFlagsTransferMask_ = ImGuiDockNodeFlags_LocalFlagsMask_ & ~ImGuiDockNodeFlags_DockSpace, // When splitting those flags are moved to the inheriting child, never duplicated
1470 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_SavedFlagsMask_ = ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoResizeFlagsMask_ | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_DockSpace | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_CentralNode | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoTabBar | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_HiddenTabBar | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoWindowMenuButton | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoCloseButton | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoDocking
1471};

1489// sizeof() 156~192
1490struct IMGUI_API ImGuiDockNode
1491{
1492 ImGuiID ID;
1493 ImGuiDockNodeFlags SharedFlags; // (Write) Flags shared by all nodes of a same dockspace hierarchy (inherited from the root node)
1494 ImGuiDockNodeFlags LocalFlags; // (Write) Flags specific to this node
1495 ImGuiDockNodeFlags LocalFlagsInWindows; // (Write) Flags specific to this node, applied from windows
1496 ImGuiDockNodeFlags MergedFlags; // (Read) Effective flags (== SharedFlags | LocalFlagsInNode | LocalFlagsInWindows)
1497 ImGuiDockNodeState State;
1498 ImGuiDockNode* ParentNode;
1499 ImGuiDockNode* ChildNodes[2]; // [Split node only] Child nodes (left/right or top/bottom). Consider switching to an array.
1500 ImVector<ImGuiWindow*> Windows; // Note: unordered list! Iterate TabBar->Tabs for user-order.
1501 ImGuiTabBar* TabBar;
1502 ImVec2 Pos; // Current position
1503 ImVec2 Size; // Current size
1504 ImVec2 SizeRef; // [Split node only] Last explicitly written-to size (overridden when using a splitter affecting the node), used to calculate Size.
1505 ImGuiAxis SplitAxis; // [Split node only] Split axis (X or Y)
1506 ImGuiWindowClass WindowClass; // [Root node only]
1507 ImU32 LastBgColor;
1508
1509 ImGuiWindow* HostWindow;
1510 ImGuiWindow* VisibleWindow; // Generally point to window which is ID is == SelectedTabID, but when CTRL+Tabbing this can be a different window.
1511 ImGuiDockNode* CentralNode; // [Root node only] Pointer to central node.
1512 ImGuiDockNode* OnlyNodeWithWindows; // [Root node only] Set when there is a single visible node within the hierarchy.
1513 int CountNodeWithWindows; // [Root node only]
1514 int LastFrameAlive; // Last frame number the node was updated or kept alive explicitly with DockSpace() + ImGuiDockNodeFlags_KeepAliveOnly
1515 int LastFrameActive; // Last frame number the node was updated.
1516 int LastFrameFocused; // Last frame number the node was focused.
1517 ImGuiID LastFocusedNodeId; // [Root node only] Which of our child docking node (any ancestor in the hierarchy) was last focused.
1518 ImGuiID SelectedTabId; // [Leaf node only] Which of our tab/window is selected.
1519 ImGuiID WantCloseTabId; // [Leaf node only] Set when closing a specific tab/window.
1520 ImGuiDataAuthority AuthorityForPos :3;
1521 ImGuiDataAuthority AuthorityForSize :3;
1522 ImGuiDataAuthority AuthorityForViewport :3;
1523 bool IsVisible :1; // Set to false when the node is hidden (usually disabled as it has no active window)
1524 bool IsFocused :1;
1525 bool IsBgDrawnThisFrame :1;
1526 bool HasCloseButton :1; // Provide space for a close button (if any of the docked window has one). Note that button may be hidden on window without one.
1527 bool HasWindowMenuButton :1;
1528 bool HasCentralNodeChild :1;
1529 bool WantCloseAll :1; // Set when closing all tabs at once.
1530 bool WantLockSizeOnce :1;
1531 bool WantMouseMove :1; // After a node extraction we need to transition toward moving the newly created host window
1532 bool WantHiddenTabBarUpdate :1;
1533 bool WantHiddenTabBarToggle :1;
1534
1535 ImGuiDockNode(ImGuiID id);
1536 ~ImGuiDockNode();
1537 bool IsRootNode() const { return ParentNode == NULL; }
1538 bool IsDockSpace() const { return (MergedFlags & ImGuiDockNodeFlags_DockSpace) != 0; }
1539 bool IsFloatingNode() const { return ParentNode == NULL && (MergedFlags & ImGuiDockNodeFlags_DockSpace) == 0; }
1540 bool IsCentralNode() const { return (MergedFlags & ImGuiDockNodeFlags_CentralNode) != 0; }
1541 bool IsHiddenTabBar() const { return (MergedFlags & ImGuiDockNodeFlags_HiddenTabBar) != 0; } // Hidden tab bar can be shown back by clicking the small triangle
1542 bool IsNoTabBar() const { return (MergedFlags & ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoTabBar) != 0; } // Never show a tab bar
1543 bool IsSplitNode() const { return ChildNodes[0] != NULL; }
1544 bool IsLeafNode() const { return ChildNodes[0] == NULL; }
1545 bool IsEmpty() const { return ChildNodes[0] == NULL && Windows.Size == 0; }
1546 ImRect Rect() const { return ImRect(Pos.x, Pos.y, Pos.x + Size.x, Pos.y + Size.y); }
1547
1548 void SetLocalFlags(ImGuiDockNodeFlags flags) { LocalFlags = flags; UpdateMergedFlags(); }
1549 void UpdateMergedFlags() { MergedFlags = SharedFlags | LocalFlags | LocalFlagsInWindows; }
1550};

1583//-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1584// [SECTION] Viewport support
1585//-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1586
1587// ImGuiViewport Private/Internals fields (cardinal sin: we are using inheritance!)
1588// Every instance of ImGuiViewport is in fact a ImGuiViewportP.
1589struct ImGuiViewportP : public ImGuiViewport
1590{
1591 int Idx;
1592 int LastFrameActive; // Last frame number this viewport was activated by a window
1593 int LastFrontMostStampCount;// Last stamp number from when a window hosted by this viewport was made front-most (by comparing this value between two viewport we have an implicit viewport z-order
1594 ImGuiID LastNameHash;
1595 ImVec2 LastPos;
1596 float Alpha; // Window opacity (when dragging dockable windows/viewports we make them transparent)
1597 float LastAlpha;
1598 short PlatformMonitor;
1599 bool PlatformWindowCreated;
1600 ImGuiWindow* Window; // Set when the viewport is owned by a window (and ImGuiViewportFlags_CanHostOtherWindows is NOT set)
1601 int DrawListsLastFrame[2]; // Last frame number the background (0) and foreground (1) draw lists were used
1602 ImDrawList* DrawLists[2]; // Convenience background (0) and foreground (1) draw lists. We use them to draw software mouser cursor when io.MouseDrawCursor is set and to draw most debug overlays.
1603 ImDrawData DrawDataP;
1604 ImDrawDataBuilder DrawDataBuilder;
1605 ImVec2 LastPlatformPos;
1606 ImVec2 LastPlatformSize;
1607 ImVec2 LastRendererSize;
1608 ImVec2 WorkOffsetMin; // Work Area: Offset from Pos to top-left corner of Work Area. Generally (0,0) or (0,+main_menu_bar_height). Work Area is Full Area but without menu-bars/status-bars (so WorkArea always fit inside Pos/Size!)
1609 ImVec2 WorkOffsetMax; // Work Area: Offset from Pos+Size to bottom-right corner of Work Area. Generally (0,0) or (0,-status_bar_height).
1610 ImVec2 BuildWorkOffsetMin; // Work Area: Offset being built during current frame. Generally >= 0.0f.
1611 ImVec2 BuildWorkOffsetMax; // Work Area: Offset being built during current frame. Generally <= 0.0f.
1612
1613 ImGuiViewportP() { Idx = -1; LastFrameActive = DrawListsLastFrame[0] = DrawListsLastFrame[1] = LastFrontMostStampCount = -1; LastNameHash = 0; Alpha = LastAlpha = 1.0f; PlatformMonitor = -1; PlatformWindowCreated = false; Window = NULL; DrawLists[0] = DrawLists[1] = NULL; LastPlatformPos = LastPlatformSize = LastRendererSize = ImVec2(FLT_MAX, FLT_MAX); }
1614 ~ImGuiViewportP() { if (DrawLists[0]) IM_DELETE(DrawLists[0]); if (DrawLists[1]) IM_DELETE(DrawLists[1]); }
1615 void ClearRequestFlags() { PlatformRequestClose = PlatformRequestMove = PlatformRequestResize = false; }
1616
1617 // Calculate work rect pos/size given a set of offset (we have 1 pair of offset for rect locked from last frame data, and 1 pair for currently building rect)
1618 ImVec2 CalcWorkRectPos(const ImVec2& off_min) const { return ImVec2(Pos.x + off_min.x, Pos.y + off_min.y); }
1619 ImVec2 CalcWorkRectSize(const ImVec2& off_min, const ImVec2& off_max) const { return ImVec2(ImMax(0.0f, Size.x - off_min.x + off_max.x), ImMax(0.0f, Size.y - off_min.y + off_max.y)); }
1620 void UpdateWorkRect() { WorkPos = CalcWorkRectPos(WorkOffsetMin); WorkSize = CalcWorkRectSize(WorkOffsetMin, WorkOffsetMax); } // Update public fields
1621
1622 // Helpers to retrieve ImRect (we don't need to store BuildWorkRect as every access tend to change it, hence the code asymmetry)
1623 ImRect GetMainRect() const { return ImRect(Pos.x, Pos.y, Pos.x + Size.x, Pos.y + Size.y); }
1624 ImRect GetWorkRect() const { return ImRect(WorkPos.x, WorkPos.y, WorkPos.x + WorkSize.x, WorkPos.y + WorkSize.y); }
1625 ImRect GetBuildWorkRect() const { ImVec2 pos = CalcWorkRectPos(BuildWorkOffsetMin); ImVec2 size = CalcWorkRectSize(BuildWorkOffsetMin, BuildWorkOffsetMax); return ImRect(pos.x, pos.y, pos.x + size.x, pos.y + size.y); }
1626};
1627
1628//-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1629// [SECTION] Settings support
1630//-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1631
1632// Windows data saved in imgui.ini file
1633// Because we never destroy or rename ImGuiWindowSettings, we can store the names in a separate buffer easily.
1634// (this is designed to be stored in a ImChunkStream buffer, with the variable-length Name following our structure)
1635struct ImGuiWindowSettings
1636{
1637 ImGuiID ID;
1638 ImVec2ih Pos; // NB: Settings position are stored RELATIVE to the viewport! Whereas runtime ones are absolute positions.
1639 ImVec2ih Size;
1640 ImVec2ih ViewportPos;
1641 ImGuiID ViewportId;
1642 ImGuiID DockId; // ID of last known DockNode (even if the DockNode is invisible because it has only 1 active window), or 0 if none.
1643 ImGuiID ClassId; // ID of window class if specified
1644 short DockOrder; // Order of the last time the window was visible within its DockNode. This is used to reorder windows that are reappearing on the same frame. Same value between windows that were active and windows that were none are possible.
1645 bool Collapsed;
1646 bool WantApply; // Set when loaded from .ini data (to enable merging/loading .ini data into an already running context)
1647
1648 ImGuiWindowSettings() { memset(this, 0, sizeof(*this)); DockOrder = -1; }
1649 char* GetName() { return (char*)(this + 1); }
1650};
1651
1652struct ImGuiSettingsHandler
1653{
1654 const char* TypeName; // Short description stored in .ini file. Disallowed characters: '[' ']'
1655 ImGuiID TypeHash; // == ImHashStr(TypeName)
1656 void (*ClearAllFn)(ImGuiContext* ctx, ImGuiSettingsHandler* handler); // Clear all settings data
1657 void (*ReadInitFn)(ImGuiContext* ctx, ImGuiSettingsHandler* handler); // Read: Called before reading (in registration order)
1658 void* (*ReadOpenFn)(ImGuiContext* ctx, ImGuiSettingsHandler* handler, const char* name); // Read: Called when entering into a new ini entry e.g. "[Window][Name]"
1659 void (*ReadLineFn)(ImGuiContext* ctx, ImGuiSettingsHandler* handler, void* entry, const char* line); // Read: Called for every line of text within an ini entry
1660 void (*ApplyAllFn)(ImGuiContext* ctx, ImGuiSettingsHandler* handler); // Read: Called after reading (in registration order)
1661 void (*WriteAllFn)(ImGuiContext* ctx, ImGuiSettingsHandler* handler, ImGuiTextBuffer* out_buf); // Write: Output every entries into 'out_buf'
1662 void* UserData;
1663
1664 ImGuiSettingsHandler() { memset(this, 0, sizeof(*this)); }
1665};

2198// Transient per-window data, reset at the beginning of the frame. This used to be called ImGuiDrawContext, hence the DC variable name in ImGuiWindow.
2199// (That's theory, in practice the delimitation between ImGuiWindow and ImGuiWindowTempData is quite tenuous and could be reconsidered..)
2200// (This doesn't need a constructor because we zero-clear it as part of ImGuiWindow and all frame-temporary data are setup on Begin)
2201struct IMGUI_API ImGuiWindowTempData
2202{
2203 // Layout
2204 ImVec2 CursorPos; // Current emitting position, in absolute coordinates.
2205 ImVec2 CursorPosPrevLine;
2206 ImVec2 CursorStartPos; // Initial position after Begin(), generally ~ window position + WindowPadding.
2207 ImVec2 CursorMaxPos; // Used to implicitly calculate ContentSize at the beginning of next frame, for scrolling range and auto-resize. Always growing during the frame.
2208 ImVec2 IdealMaxPos; // Used to implicitly calculate ContentSizeIdeal at the beginning of next frame, for auto-resize only. Always growing during the frame.
2209 ImVec2 CurrLineSize;
2210 ImVec2 PrevLineSize;
2211 float CurrLineTextBaseOffset; // Baseline offset (0.0f by default on a new line, generally == style.FramePadding.y when a framed item has been added).
2212 float PrevLineTextBaseOffset;
2213 bool IsSameLine;
2214 ImVec1 Indent; // Indentation / start position from left of window (increased by TreePush/TreePop, etc.)
2215 ImVec1 ColumnsOffset; // Offset to the current column (if ColumnsCurrent > 0). FIXME: This and the above should be a stack to allow use cases like Tree->Column->Tree. Need revamp columns API.
2216 ImVec1 GroupOffset;
2217 ImVec2 CursorStartPosLossyness;// Record the loss of precision of CursorStartPos due to really large scrolling amount. This is used by clipper to compensentate and fix the most common use case of large scroll area.
2218
2219 // Keyboard/Gamepad navigation
2220 ImGuiNavLayer NavLayerCurrent; // Current layer, 0..31 (we currently only use 0..1)
2221 short NavLayersActiveMask; // Which layers have been written to (result from previous frame)
2222 short NavLayersActiveMaskNext;// Which layers have been written to (accumulator for current frame)
2223 ImGuiID NavFocusScopeIdCurrent; // Current focus scope ID while appending
2224 bool NavHideHighlightOneFrame;
2225 bool NavHasScroll; // Set when scrolling can be used (ScrollMax > 0.0f)
2226
2227 // Miscellaneous
2228 bool MenuBarAppending; // FIXME: Remove this
2229 ImVec2 MenuBarOffset; // MenuBarOffset.x is sort of equivalent of a per-layer CursorPos.x, saved/restored as we switch to the menu bar. The only situation when MenuBarOffset.y is > 0 if when (SafeAreaPadding.y > FramePadding.y), often used on TVs.
2230 ImGuiMenuColumns MenuColumns; // Simplified columns storage for menu items measurement
2231 int TreeDepth; // Current tree depth.
2232 ImU32 TreeJumpToParentOnPopMask; // Store a copy of !g.NavIdIsAlive for TreeDepth 0..31.. Could be turned into a ImU64 if necessary.
2233 ImVector<ImGuiWindow*> ChildWindows;
2234 ImGuiStorage* StateStorage; // Current persistent per-window storage (store e.g. tree node open/close state)
2235 ImGuiOldColumns* CurrentColumns; // Current columns set
2236 int CurrentTableIdx; // Current table index (into g.Tables)
2237 ImGuiLayoutType LayoutType;
2238 ImGuiLayoutType ParentLayoutType; // Layout type of parent window at the time of Begin()
2239
2240 // Local parameters stacks
2241 // We store the current settings outside of the vectors to increase memory locality (reduce cache misses). The vectors are rarely modified. Also it allows us to not heap allocate for short-lived windows which are not using those settings.
2242 float ItemWidth; // Current item width (>0.0: width in pixels, <0.0: align xx pixels to the right of window).
2243 float TextWrapPos; // Current text wrap pos.
2244 ImVector<float> ItemWidthStack; // Store item widths to restore (attention: .back() is not == ItemWidth)
2245 ImVector<float> TextWrapPosStack; // Store text wrap pos to restore (attention: .back() is not == TextWrapPos)
2246};

2248// Storage for one window
2249struct IMGUI_API ImGuiWindow
2250{
2251 char* Name; // Window name, owned by the window.
2252 ImGuiID ID; // == ImHashStr(Name)
2253 ImGuiWindowFlags Flags, FlagsPreviousFrame; // See enum ImGuiWindowFlags_
2254 ImGuiWindowClass WindowClass; // Advanced users only. Set with SetNextWindowClass()
2255 ImGuiViewportP* Viewport; // Always set in Begin(). Inactive windows may have a NULL value here if their viewport was discarded.
2256 ImGuiID ViewportId; // We backup the viewport id (since the viewport may disappear or never be created if the window is inactive)
2257 ImVec2 ViewportPos; // We backup the viewport position (since the viewport may disappear or never be created if the window is inactive)
2258 int ViewportAllowPlatformMonitorExtend; // Reset to -1 every frame (index is guaranteed to be valid between NewFrame..EndFrame), only used in the Appearing frame of a tooltip/popup to enforce clamping to a given monitor
2259 ImVec2 Pos; // Position (always rounded-up to nearest pixel)
2260 ImVec2 Size; // Current size (==SizeFull or collapsed title bar size)
2261 ImVec2 SizeFull; // Size when non collapsed
2262 ImVec2 ContentSize; // Size of contents/scrollable client area (calculated from the extents reach of the cursor) from previous frame. Does not include window decoration or window padding.
2263 ImVec2 ContentSizeIdeal;
2264 ImVec2 ContentSizeExplicit; // Size of contents/scrollable client area explicitly request by the user via SetNextWindowContentSize().
2265 ImVec2 WindowPadding; // Window padding at the time of Begin().
2266 float WindowRounding; // Window rounding at the time of Begin(). May be clamped lower to avoid rendering artifacts with title bar, menu bar etc.
2267 float WindowBorderSize; // Window border size at the time of Begin().
2268 int NameBufLen; // Size of buffer storing Name. May be larger than strlen(Name)!
2269 ImGuiID MoveId; // == window->GetID("#MOVE")
2270 ImGuiID TabId; // == window->GetID("#TAB")
2271 ImGuiID ChildId; // ID of corresponding item in parent window (for navigation to return from child window to parent window)
2272 ImVec2 Scroll;
2273 ImVec2 ScrollMax;
2274 ImVec2 ScrollTarget; // target scroll position. stored as cursor position with scrolling canceled out, so the highest point is always 0.0f. (FLT_MAX for no change)
2275 ImVec2 ScrollTargetCenterRatio; // 0.0f = scroll so that target position is at top, 0.5f = scroll so that target position is centered
2276 ImVec2 ScrollTargetEdgeSnapDist; // 0.0f = no snapping, >0.0f snapping threshold
2277 ImVec2 ScrollbarSizes; // Size taken by each scrollbars on their smaller axis. Pay attention! ScrollbarSizes.x == width of the vertical scrollbar, ScrollbarSizes.y = height of the horizontal scrollbar.
2278 bool ScrollbarX, ScrollbarY; // Are scrollbars visible?
2279 bool ViewportOwned;
2280 bool Active; // Set to true on Begin(), unless Collapsed
2281 bool WasActive;
2282 bool WriteAccessed; // Set to true when any widget access the current window
2283 bool Collapsed; // Set when collapsing window to become only title-bar
2284 bool WantCollapseToggle;
2285 bool SkipItems; // Set when items can safely be all clipped (e.g. window not visible or collapsed)
2286 bool Appearing; // Set during the frame where the window is appearing (or re-appearing)
2287 bool Hidden; // Do not display (== HiddenFrames*** > 0)
2288 bool IsFallbackWindow; // Set on the "Debug##Default" window.
2289 bool IsExplicitChild; // Set when passed _ChildWindow, left to false by BeginDocked()
2290 bool HasCloseButton; // Set when the window has a close button (p_open != NULL)
2291 signed char ResizeBorderHeld; // Current border being held for resize (-1: none, otherwise 0-3)
2292 short BeginCount; // Number of Begin() during the current frame (generally 0 or 1, 1+ if appending via multiple Begin/End pairs)
2293 short BeginOrderWithinParent; // Begin() order within immediate parent window, if we are a child window. Otherwise 0.
2294 short BeginOrderWithinContext; // Begin() order within entire imgui context. This is mostly used for debugging submission order related issues.
2295 short FocusOrder; // Order within WindowsFocusOrder[], altered when windows are focused.
2296 ImGuiID PopupId; // ID in the popup stack when this window is used as a popup/menu (because we use generic Name/ID for recycling)
2297 ImS8 AutoFitFramesX, AutoFitFramesY;
2298 ImS8 AutoFitChildAxises;
2299 bool AutoFitOnlyGrows;
2300 ImGuiDir AutoPosLastDirection;
2301 ImS8 HiddenFramesCanSkipItems; // Hide the window for N frames
2302 ImS8 HiddenFramesCannotSkipItems; // Hide the window for N frames while allowing items to be submitted so we can measure their size
2303 ImS8 HiddenFramesForRenderOnly; // Hide the window until frame N at Render() time only
2304 ImS8 DisableInputsFrames; // Disable window interactions for N frames
2305 ImGuiCond SetWindowPosAllowFlags : 8; // store acceptable condition flags for SetNextWindowPos() use.
2306 ImGuiCond SetWindowSizeAllowFlags : 8; // store acceptable condition flags for SetNextWindowSize() use.
2307 ImGuiCond SetWindowCollapsedAllowFlags : 8; // store acceptable condition flags for SetNextWindowCollapsed() use.
2308 ImGuiCond SetWindowDockAllowFlags : 8; // store acceptable condition flags for SetNextWindowDock() use.
2309 ImVec2 SetWindowPosVal; // store window position when using a non-zero Pivot (position set needs to be processed when we know the window size)
2310 ImVec2 SetWindowPosPivot; // store window pivot for positioning. ImVec2(0, 0) when positioning from top-left corner; ImVec2(0.5f, 0.5f) for centering; ImVec2(1, 1) for bottom right.
2311
2312 ImVector<ImGuiID> IDStack; // ID stack. ID are hashes seeded with the value at the top of the stack. (In theory this should be in the TempData structure)
2313 ImGuiWindowTempData DC; // Temporary per-window data, reset at the beginning of the frame. This used to be called ImGuiDrawContext, hence the "DC" variable name.
2314
2315 // The best way to understand what those rectangles are is to use the 'Metrics->Tools->Show Windows Rectangles' viewer.
2316 // The main 'OuterRect', omitted as a field, is window->Rect().
2317 ImRect OuterRectClipped; // == Window->Rect() just after setup in Begin(). == window->Rect() for root window.
2318 ImRect InnerRect; // Inner rectangle (omit title bar, menu bar, scroll bar)
2319 ImRect InnerClipRect; // == InnerRect shrunk by WindowPadding*0.5f on each side, clipped within viewport or parent clip rect.
2320 ImRect WorkRect; // Initially covers the whole scrolling region. Reduced by containers e.g columns/tables when active. Shrunk by WindowPadding*1.0f on each side. This is meant to replace ContentRegionRect over time (from 1.71+ onward).
2321 ImRect ParentWorkRect; // Backup of WorkRect before entering a container such as columns/tables. Used by e.g. SpanAllColumns functions to easily access. Stacked containers are responsible for maintaining this. // FIXME-WORKRECT: Could be a stack?
2322 ImRect ClipRect; // Current clipping/scissoring rectangle, evolve as we are using PushClipRect(), etc. == DrawList->clip_rect_stack.back().
2323 ImRect ContentRegionRect; // FIXME: This is currently confusing/misleading. It is essentially WorkRect but not handling of scrolling. We currently rely on it as right/bottom aligned sizing operation need some size to rely on.
2324 ImVec2ih HitTestHoleSize; // Define an optional rectangular hole where mouse will pass-through the window.
2325 ImVec2ih HitTestHoleOffset;
2326
2327 int LastFrameActive; // Last frame number the window was Active.
2328 int LastFrameJustFocused; // Last frame number the window was made Focused.
2329 float LastTimeActive; // Last timestamp the window was Active (using float as we don't need high precision there)
2330 float ItemWidthDefault;
2331 ImGuiStorage StateStorage;
2332 ImVector<ImGuiOldColumns> ColumnsStorage;
2333 float FontWindowScale; // User scale multiplier per-window, via SetWindowFontScale()
2334 float FontDpiScale;
2335 int SettingsOffset; // Offset into SettingsWindows[] (offsets are always valid as we only grow the array from the back)
2336

2338 ImDrawList DrawListInst;
2339 ImGuiWindow* ParentWindow; // If we are a child _or_ popup _or_ docked window, this is pointing to our parent. Otherwise NULL.
2340 ImGuiWindow* ParentWindowInBeginStack;

2342 ImGuiWindow* RootWindowPopupTree; // Point to ourself or first ancestor that is not a child window. Cross through popups parent<>child.
2343 ImGuiWindow* RootWindowDockTree; // Point to ourself or first ancestor that is not a child window. Cross through dock nodes.

2346

2349 ImRect NavRectRel[ImGuiNavLayer_COUNT]; // Reference rectangle, in window relative space

2352 int MemoryDrawListVtxCapacity;
2353 bool MemoryCompacted; // Set when window extraneous data have been garbage collected
2354
2355 // Docking
2356 bool DockIsActive :1; // When docking artifacts are actually visible. When this is set, DockNode is guaranteed to be != NULL. ~~ (DockNode != NULL) && (DockNode->Windows.Size > 1).
2357 bool DockNodeIsVisible :1;
2358 bool DockTabIsVisible :1; // Is our window visible this frame? ~~ is the corresponding tab selected?
2359 bool DockTabWantClose :1;
2360 short DockOrder; // Order of the last time the window was visible within its DockNode. This is used to reorder windows that are reappearing on the same frame. Same value between windows that were active and windows that were none are possible.
2361 ImGuiWindowDockStyle DockStyle;
2362 ImGuiDockNode* DockNode; // Which node are we docked into. Important: Prefer testing DockIsActive in many cases as this will still be set when the dock node is hidden.
2363 ImGuiDockNode* DockNodeAsHost; // Which node are we owning (for parent windows)
2364 ImGuiID DockId; // Backup of last valid DockNode->ID, so single window remember their dock node id even when they are not bound any more
2365 ImGuiItemStatusFlags DockTabItemStatusFlags;
2366 ImRect DockTabItemRect;
2367
2368public:
2369 ImGuiWindow(ImGuiContext* context, const char* name);
2370 ~ImGuiWindow();
2371
2372 ImGuiID GetID(const char* str, const char* str_end = NULL);
2373 ImGuiID GetID(const void* ptr);
2374 ImGuiID GetID(int n);
2375 ImGuiID GetIDFromRectangle(const ImRect& r_abs);
2376
2377 // We don't use g.FontSize because the window may be != g.CurrentWidow.
2378 ImRect Rect() const { return ImRect(Pos.x, Pos.y, Pos.x + Size.x, Pos.y + Size.y); }
2379 float CalcFontSize() const { ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui; float scale = g.FontBaseSize * FontWindowScale * FontDpiScale; if (ParentWindow) scale *= ParentWindow->FontWindowScale; return scale; }
2380 float TitleBarHeight() const { ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui; return (Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoTitleBar) ? 0.0f : CalcFontSize() + g.Style.FramePadding.y * 2.0f; }
2381 ImRect TitleBarRect() const { return ImRect(Pos, ImVec2(Pos.x + SizeFull.x, Pos.y + TitleBarHeight())); }
2382 float MenuBarHeight() const { ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui; return (Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_MenuBar) ? DC.MenuBarOffset.y + CalcFontSize() + g.Style.FramePadding.y * 2.0f : 0.0f; }
2383 ImRect MenuBarRect() const { float y1 = Pos.y + TitleBarHeight(); return ImRect(Pos.x, y1, Pos.x + SizeFull.x, y1 + MenuBarHeight()); }

2392{

2394 ImGuiTabBarFlags_IsFocused = 1 << 21,
2395 ImGuiTabBarFlags_SaveSettings = 1 << 22 // FIXME: Settings are handled by the docking system, this only request the tab bar to mark settings dirty when reordering tabs
2396};

2398// Extend ImGuiTabItemFlags_
2399enum ImGuiTabItemFlagsPrivate_
2400{
2401 ImGuiTabItemFlags_SectionMask_ = ImGuiTabItemFlags_Leading | ImGuiTabItemFlags_Trailing,
2402 ImGuiTabItemFlags_NoCloseButton = 1 << 20, // Track whether p_open was set or not (we'll need this info on the next frame to recompute ContentWidth during layout)
2403 ImGuiTabItemFlags_Button = 1 << 21, // Used by TabItemButton, change the tab item behavior to mimic a button
2404 ImGuiTabItemFlags_Unsorted = 1 << 22, // [Docking] Trailing tabs with the _Unsorted flag will be sorted based on the DockOrder of their Window.
2405 ImGuiTabItemFlags_Preview = 1 << 23 // [Docking] Display tab shape for docking preview (height is adjusted slightly to compensate for the yet missing tab bar)
2406};

2408// Storage for one active tab item (sizeof() 48 bytes)
2409struct ImGuiTabItem
2410{
2411 ImGuiID ID;
2412 ImGuiTabItemFlags Flags;
2413 ImGuiWindow* Window; // When TabItem is part of a DockNode's TabBar, we hold on to a window.
2414 int LastFrameVisible;
2415 int LastFrameSelected; // This allows us to infer an ordered list of the last activated tabs with little maintenance
2416 float Offset; // Position relative to beginning of tab
2417 float Width; // Width currently displayed
2418 float ContentWidth; // Width of label, stored during BeginTabItem() call
2419 float RequestedWidth; // Width optionally requested by caller, -1.0f is unused
2420 ImS32 NameOffset; // When Window==NULL, offset to name within parent ImGuiTabBar::TabsNames
2421 ImS16 BeginOrder; // BeginTabItem() order, used to re-order tabs after toggling ImGuiTabBarFlags_Reorderable
2422 ImS16 IndexDuringLayout; // Index only used during TabBarLayout()
2423 bool WantClose; // Marked as closed by SetTabItemClosed()
2424
2425 ImGuiTabItem() { memset(this, 0, sizeof(*this)); LastFrameVisible = LastFrameSelected = -1; NameOffset = -1; BeginOrder = IndexDuringLayout = -1; }
2426};

2428// Storage for a tab bar (sizeof() 152 bytes)
2429struct IMGUI_API ImGuiTabBar
2430{

2432 ImGuiTabBarFlags Flags;
2433 ImGuiID ID; // Zero for tab-bars used by docking

2435 ImGuiID NextSelectedTabId; // Next selected tab/window. Will also trigger a scrolling animation
2436 ImGuiID VisibleTabId; // Can occasionally be != SelectedTabId (e.g. when previewing contents for CTRL+TAB preview)
2437 int CurrFrameVisible;
2438 int PrevFrameVisible;
2439 ImRect BarRect;
2440 float CurrTabsContentsHeight;
2441 float PrevTabsContentsHeight; // Record the height of contents submitted below the tab bar
2442 float WidthAllTabs; // Actual width of all tabs (locked during layout)
2443 float WidthAllTabsIdeal; // Ideal width if all tabs were visible and not clipped
2444 float ScrollingAnim;
2445 float ScrollingTarget;

2449 float ScrollingRectMaxX;
2450 ImGuiID ReorderRequestTabId;

2452 ImS8 BeginCount;
2453 bool WantLayout;
2454 bool VisibleTabWasSubmitted;
2455 bool TabsAddedNew; // Set to true when a new tab item or button has been added to the tab bar during last frame
2456 ImS16 TabsActiveCount; // Number of tabs submitted this frame.
2457 ImS16 LastTabItemIdx; // Index of last BeginTabItem() tab for use by EndTabItem()
2458 float ItemSpacingY;
2459 ImVec2 FramePadding; // style.FramePadding locked at the time of BeginTabBar()
2460 ImVec2 BackupCursorPos;
2461 ImGuiTextBuffer TabsNames; // For non-docking tab bar we re-append names in a contiguous buffer.
2462
2463 ImGuiTabBar();
2464 int GetTabOrder(const ImGuiTabItem* tab) const { return Tabs.index_from_ptr(tab); }
2465 const char* GetTabName(const ImGuiTabItem* tab) const
2466 {
2467 if (tab->Window)
2468 return tab->Window->Name;
2469 IM_ASSERT(tab->NameOffset != -1 && tab->NameOffset < TabsNames.Buf.Size);
2470 return TabsNames.Buf.Data + tab->NameOffset;
2471 }

2474//-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
2475// [SECTION] Table support
2476//-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
2477
2478#define IM_COL32_DISABLE IM_COL32(0,0,0,1) // Special sentinel code which cannot be used as a regular color.
2479#define IMGUI_TABLE_MAX_COLUMNS 64 // sizeof(ImU64) * 8. This is solely because we frequently encode columns set in a ImU64.
2480#define IMGUI_TABLE_MAX_DRAW_CHANNELS (4 + 64 * 2) // See TableSetupDrawChannels()
2481
2482// Our current column maximum is 64 but we may raise that in the future.
2483typedef ImS8 ImGuiTableColumnIdx;
2484typedef ImU8 ImGuiTableDrawChannelIdx;
2485
2486// [Internal] sizeof() ~ 104
2487// We use the terminology "Enabled" to refer to a column that is not Hidden by user/api.
2488// We use the terminology "Clipped" to refer to a column that is out of sight because of scrolling/clipping.
2489// This is in contrast with some user-facing api such as IsItemVisible() / IsRectVisible() which use "Visible" to mean "not clipped".
2490struct ImGuiTableColumn
2491{
2492 ImGuiTableColumnFlags Flags; // Flags after some patching (not directly same as provided by user). See ImGuiTableColumnFlags_
2493 float WidthGiven; // Final/actual width visible == (MaxX - MinX), locked in TableUpdateLayout(). May be > WidthRequest to honor minimum width, may be < WidthRequest to honor shrinking columns down in tight space.
2494 float MinX; // Absolute positions
2495 float MaxX;
2496 float WidthRequest; // Master width absolute value when !(Flags & _WidthStretch). When Stretch this is derived every frame from StretchWeight in TableUpdateLayout()
2497 float WidthAuto; // Automatic width
2498 float StretchWeight; // Master width weight when (Flags & _WidthStretch). Often around ~1.0f initially.
2499 float InitStretchWeightOrWidth; // Value passed to TableSetupColumn(). For Width it is a content width (_without padding_).
2500 ImRect ClipRect; // Clipping rectangle for the column
2501 ImGuiID UserID; // Optional, value passed to TableSetupColumn()
2502 float WorkMinX; // Contents region min ~(MinX + CellPaddingX + CellSpacingX1) == cursor start position when entering column
2503 float WorkMaxX; // Contents region max ~(MaxX - CellPaddingX - CellSpacingX2)
2504 float ItemWidth; // Current item width for the column, preserved across rows
2505 float ContentMaxXFrozen; // Contents maximum position for frozen rows (apart from headers), from which we can infer content width.
2506 float ContentMaxXUnfrozen;
2507 float ContentMaxXHeadersUsed; // Contents maximum position for headers rows (regardless of freezing). TableHeader() automatically softclip itself + report ideal desired size, to avoid creating extraneous draw calls
2508 float ContentMaxXHeadersIdeal;
2509 ImS16 NameOffset; // Offset into parent ColumnsNames[]
2510 ImGuiTableColumnIdx DisplayOrder; // Index within Table's IndexToDisplayOrder[] (column may be reordered by users)
2511 ImGuiTableColumnIdx IndexWithinEnabledSet; // Index within enabled/visible set (<= IndexToDisplayOrder)
2512 ImGuiTableColumnIdx PrevEnabledColumn; // Index of prev enabled/visible column within Columns[], -1 if first enabled/visible column
2513 ImGuiTableColumnIdx NextEnabledColumn; // Index of next enabled/visible column within Columns[], -1 if last enabled/visible column
2514 ImGuiTableColumnIdx SortOrder; // Index of this column within sort specs, -1 if not sorting on this column, 0 for single-sort, may be >0 on multi-sort
2515 ImGuiTableDrawChannelIdx DrawChannelCurrent; // Index within DrawSplitter.Channels[]
2516 ImGuiTableDrawChannelIdx DrawChannelFrozen; // Draw channels for frozen rows (often headers)
2517 ImGuiTableDrawChannelIdx DrawChannelUnfrozen; // Draw channels for unfrozen rows
2518 bool IsEnabled; // IsUserEnabled && (Flags & ImGuiTableColumnFlags_Disabled) == 0
2519 bool IsUserEnabled; // Is the column not marked Hidden by the user? (unrelated to being off view, e.g. clipped by scrolling).
2520 bool IsUserEnabledNextFrame;
2521 bool IsVisibleX; // Is actually in view (e.g. overlapping the host window clipping rectangle, not scrolled).
2522 bool IsVisibleY;
2523 bool IsRequestOutput; // Return value for TableSetColumnIndex() / TableNextColumn(): whether we request user to output contents or not.
2524 bool IsSkipItems; // Do we want item submissions to this column to be completely ignored (no layout will happen).
2525 bool IsPreserveWidthAuto;
2526 ImS8 NavLayerCurrent; // ImGuiNavLayer in 1 byte
2527 ImU8 AutoFitQueue; // Queue of 8 values for the next 8 frames to request auto-fit
2528 ImU8 CannotSkipItemsQueue; // Queue of 8 values for the next 8 frames to disable Clipped/SkipItem
2529 ImU8 SortDirection : 2; // ImGuiSortDirection_Ascending or ImGuiSortDirection_Descending
2530 ImU8 SortDirectionsAvailCount : 2; // Number of available sort directions (0 to 3)
2531 ImU8 SortDirectionsAvailMask : 4; // Mask of available sort directions (1-bit each)
2532 ImU8 SortDirectionsAvailList; // Ordered of available sort directions (2-bits each)
2533
2534 ImGuiTableColumn()
2535 {
2536 memset(this, 0, sizeof(*this));
2537 StretchWeight = WidthRequest = -1.0f;
2538 NameOffset = -1;
2539 DisplayOrder = IndexWithinEnabledSet = -1;
2540 PrevEnabledColumn = NextEnabledColumn = -1;
2541 SortOrder = -1;
2542 SortDirection = ImGuiSortDirection_None;
2543 DrawChannelCurrent = DrawChannelFrozen = DrawChannelUnfrozen = (ImU8)-1;
2544 }
2545};
