2564// FIXME-TABLE: more transient data could be stored in a per-stacked table structure: DrawSplitter, SortSpecs, incoming RowData
2565struct IMGUI_API ImGuiTable
2566{
2567 ImGuiID ID;
2568 ImGuiTableFlags Flags;
2569 void* RawData; // Single allocation to hold Columns[], DisplayOrderToIndex[] and RowCellData[]
2570 ImGuiTableTempData* TempData; // Transient data while table is active. Point within g.CurrentTableStack[]
2571 ImSpan<ImGuiTableColumn> Columns; // Point within RawData[]
2572 ImSpan<ImGuiTableColumnIdx> DisplayOrderToIndex; // Point within RawData[]. Store display order of columns (when not reordered, the values are 0...Count-1)
2573 ImSpan<ImGuiTableCellData> RowCellData; // Point within RawData[]. Store cells background requests for current row.
2574 ImU64 EnabledMaskByDisplayOrder; // Column DisplayOrder -> IsEnabled map
2575 ImU64 EnabledMaskByIndex; // Column Index -> IsEnabled map (== not hidden by user/api) in a format adequate for iterating column without touching cold data
2576 ImU64 VisibleMaskByIndex; // Column Index -> IsVisibleX|IsVisibleY map (== not hidden by user/api && not hidden by scrolling/cliprect)
2577 ImU64 RequestOutputMaskByIndex; // Column Index -> IsVisible || AutoFit (== expect user to submit items)
2578 ImGuiTableFlags SettingsLoadedFlags; // Which data were loaded from the .ini file (e.g. when order is not altered we won't save order)
2579 int SettingsOffset; // Offset in g.SettingsTables
2580 int LastFrameActive;
2581 int ColumnsCount; // Number of columns declared in BeginTable()
2582 int CurrentRow;
2583 int CurrentColumn;
2584 ImS16 InstanceCurrent; // Count of BeginTable() calls with same ID in the same frame (generally 0). This is a little bit similar to BeginCount for a window, but multiple table with same ID look are multiple tables, they are just synched.
2585 ImS16 InstanceInteracted; // Mark which instance (generally 0) of the same ID is being interacted with
2586 float RowPosY1;
2587 float RowPosY2;
2588 float RowMinHeight; // Height submitted to TableNextRow()
2589 float RowTextBaseline;
2590 float RowIndentOffsetX;
2591 ImGuiTableRowFlags RowFlags : 16; // Current row flags, see ImGuiTableRowFlags_
2592 ImGuiTableRowFlags LastRowFlags : 16;
2593 int RowBgColorCounter; // Counter for alternating background colors (can be fast-forwarded by e.g clipper), not same as CurrentRow because header rows typically don't increase this.
2594 ImU32 RowBgColor[2]; // Background color override for current row.
2595 ImU32 BorderColorStrong;
2596 ImU32 BorderColorLight;
2597 float BorderX1;
2598 float BorderX2;
2599 float HostIndentX;
2600 float MinColumnWidth;
2601 float OuterPaddingX;
2602 float CellPaddingX; // Padding from each borders
2603 float CellPaddingY;
2604 float CellSpacingX1; // Spacing between non-bordered cells
2605 float CellSpacingX2;
2606 float InnerWidth; // User value passed to BeginTable(), see comments at the top of BeginTable() for details.
2607 float ColumnsGivenWidth; // Sum of current column width
2608 float ColumnsAutoFitWidth; // Sum of ideal column width in order nothing to be clipped, used for auto-fitting and content width submission in outer window
2609 float ColumnsStretchSumWeights; // Sum of weight of all enabled stretching columns
2610 float ResizedColumnNextWidth;
2611 float ResizeLockMinContentsX2; // Lock minimum contents width while resizing down in order to not create feedback loops. But we allow growing the table.
2612 float RefScale; // Reference scale to be able to rescale columns on font/dpi changes.
2613 ImRect OuterRect; // Note: for non-scrolling table, OuterRect.Max.y is often FLT_MAX until EndTable(), unless a height has been specified in BeginTable().
2614 ImRect InnerRect; // InnerRect but without decoration. As with OuterRect, for non-scrolling tables, InnerRect.Max.y is
2615 ImRect WorkRect;
2616 ImRect InnerClipRect;
2617 ImRect BgClipRect; // We use this to cpu-clip cell background color fill, evolve during the frame as we cross frozen rows boundaries
2618 ImRect Bg0ClipRectForDrawCmd; // Actual ImDrawCmd clip rect for BG0/1 channel. This tends to be == OuterWindow->ClipRect at BeginTable() because output in BG0/BG1 is cpu-clipped
2619 ImRect Bg2ClipRectForDrawCmd; // Actual ImDrawCmd clip rect for BG2 channel. This tends to be a correct, tight-fit, because output to BG2 are done by widgets relying on regular ClipRect.
2620 ImRect HostClipRect; // This is used to check if we can eventually merge our columns draw calls into the current draw call of the current window.
2621 ImRect HostBackupInnerClipRect; // Backup of InnerWindow->ClipRect during PushTableBackground()/PopTableBackground()
2622 ImGuiWindow* OuterWindow; // Parent window for the table
2623 ImGuiWindow* InnerWindow; // Window holding the table data (== OuterWindow or a child window)
2624 ImGuiTextBuffer ColumnsNames; // Contiguous buffer holding columns names
2625 ImDrawListSplitter* DrawSplitter; // Shortcut to TempData->DrawSplitter while in table. Isolate draw commands per columns to avoid switching clip rect constantly
2626 ImGuiTableInstanceData InstanceDataFirst;
2627 ImVector<ImGuiTableInstanceData> InstanceDataExtra; // FIXME-OPT: Using a small-vector pattern would be good.
2628 ImGuiTableColumnSortSpecs SortSpecsSingle;
2629 ImVector<ImGuiTableColumnSortSpecs> SortSpecsMulti; // FIXME-OPT: Using a small-vector pattern would be good.
2630 ImGuiTableSortSpecs SortSpecs; // Public facing sorts specs, this is what we return in TableGetSortSpecs()
2631 ImGuiTableColumnIdx SortSpecsCount;
2632 ImGuiTableColumnIdx ColumnsEnabledCount; // Number of enabled columns (<= ColumnsCount)
2633 ImGuiTableColumnIdx ColumnsEnabledFixedCount; // Number of enabled columns (<= ColumnsCount)
2634 ImGuiTableColumnIdx DeclColumnsCount; // Count calls to TableSetupColumn()
2635 ImGuiTableColumnIdx HoveredColumnBody; // Index of column whose visible region is being hovered. Important: == ColumnsCount when hovering empty region after the right-most column!
2636 ImGuiTableColumnIdx HoveredColumnBorder; // Index of column whose right-border is being hovered (for resizing).
2637 ImGuiTableColumnIdx AutoFitSingleColumn; // Index of single column requesting auto-fit.
2638 ImGuiTableColumnIdx ResizedColumn; // Index of column being resized. Reset when InstanceCurrent==0.
2639 ImGuiTableColumnIdx LastResizedColumn; // Index of column being resized from previous frame.
2640 ImGuiTableColumnIdx HeldHeaderColumn; // Index of column header being held.
2641 ImGuiTableColumnIdx ReorderColumn; // Index of column being reordered. (not cleared)
2642 ImGuiTableColumnIdx ReorderColumnDir; // -1 or +1
2643 ImGuiTableColumnIdx LeftMostEnabledColumn; // Index of left-most non-hidden column.
2644 ImGuiTableColumnIdx RightMostEnabledColumn; // Index of right-most non-hidden column.
2645 ImGuiTableColumnIdx LeftMostStretchedColumn; // Index of left-most stretched column.
2646 ImGuiTableColumnIdx RightMostStretchedColumn; // Index of right-most stretched column.
2647 ImGuiTableColumnIdx ContextPopupColumn; // Column right-clicked on, of -1 if opening context menu from a neutral/empty spot
2648 ImGuiTableColumnIdx FreezeRowsRequest; // Requested frozen rows count
2649 ImGuiTableColumnIdx FreezeRowsCount; // Actual frozen row count (== FreezeRowsRequest, or == 0 when no scrolling offset)
2650 ImGuiTableColumnIdx FreezeColumnsRequest; // Requested frozen columns count
2651 ImGuiTableColumnIdx FreezeColumnsCount; // Actual frozen columns count (== FreezeColumnsRequest, or == 0 when no scrolling offset)
2652 ImGuiTableColumnIdx RowCellDataCurrent; // Index of current RowCellData[] entry in current row
2653 ImGuiTableDrawChannelIdx DummyDrawChannel; // Redirect non-visible columns here.
2654 ImGuiTableDrawChannelIdx Bg2DrawChannelCurrent; // For Selectable() and other widgets drawing across columns after the freezing line. Index within DrawSplitter.Channels[]
2655 ImGuiTableDrawChannelIdx Bg2DrawChannelUnfrozen;
2656 bool IsLayoutLocked; // Set by TableUpdateLayout() which is called when beginning the first row.
2657 bool IsInsideRow; // Set when inside TableBeginRow()/TableEndRow().
2658 bool IsInitializing;
2659 bool IsSortSpecsDirty;
2660 bool IsUsingHeaders; // Set when the first row had the ImGuiTableRowFlags_Headers flag.
2661 bool IsContextPopupOpen; // Set when default context menu is open (also see: ContextPopupColumn, InstanceInteracted).
2662 bool IsSettingsRequestLoad;
2663 bool IsSettingsDirty; // Set when table settings have changed and needs to be reported into ImGuiTableSetttings data.
2664 bool IsDefaultDisplayOrder; // Set when display order is unchanged from default (DisplayOrder contains 0...Count-1)
2665 bool IsResetAllRequest;
2666 bool IsResetDisplayOrderRequest;
2667 bool IsUnfrozenRows; // Set when we got past the frozen row.
2668 bool IsDefaultSizingPolicy; // Set if user didn't explicitly set a sizing policy in BeginTable()
2669 bool MemoryCompacted;
2670 bool HostSkipItems; // Backup of InnerWindow->SkipItem at the end of BeginTable(), because we will overwrite InnerWindow->SkipItem on a per-column basis
2671
2672 ImGuiTable() { memset(this, 0, sizeof(*this)); LastFrameActive = -1; }
2673 ~ImGuiTable() { IM_FREE(RawData); }
2674};

2676// Transient data that are only needed between BeginTable() and EndTable(), those buffers are shared (1 per level of stacked table).
2677// - Accessing those requires chasing an extra pointer so for very frequently used data we leave them in the main table structure.
2678// - We also leave out of this structure data that tend to be particularly useful for debugging/metrics.
2679struct IMGUI_API ImGuiTableTempData
2680{
2681 int TableIndex; // Index in g.Tables.Buf[] pool
2682 float LastTimeActive; // Last timestamp this structure was used
2683
2684 ImVec2 UserOuterSize; // outer_size.x passed to BeginTable()
2685 ImDrawListSplitter DrawSplitter;
2686
2687 ImRect HostBackupWorkRect; // Backup of InnerWindow->WorkRect at the end of BeginTable()
2688 ImRect HostBackupParentWorkRect; // Backup of InnerWindow->ParentWorkRect at the end of BeginTable()
2689 ImVec2 HostBackupPrevLineSize; // Backup of InnerWindow->DC.PrevLineSize at the end of BeginTable()
2690 ImVec2 HostBackupCurrLineSize; // Backup of InnerWindow->DC.CurrLineSize at the end of BeginTable()
2691 ImVec2 HostBackupCursorMaxPos; // Backup of InnerWindow->DC.CursorMaxPos at the end of BeginTable()
2692 ImVec1 HostBackupColumnsOffset; // Backup of OuterWindow->DC.ColumnsOffset at the end of BeginTable()
2693 float HostBackupItemWidth; // Backup of OuterWindow->DC.ItemWidth at the end of BeginTable()
2694 int HostBackupItemWidthStackSize;//Backup of OuterWindow->DC.ItemWidthStack.Size at the end of BeginTable()
2695
2696 ImGuiTableTempData() { memset(this, 0, sizeof(*this)); LastTimeActive = -1.0f; }
2697};

2744 // Windows
2745 // We should always have a CurrentWindow in the stack (there is an implicit "Debug" window)
2746 // If this ever crash because g.CurrentWindow is NULL it means that either
2747 // - ImGui::NewFrame() has never been called, which is illegal.
2748 // - You are calling ImGui functions after ImGui::EndFrame()/ImGui::Render() and before the next ImGui::NewFrame(), which is also illegal.

2971 // Docking - Builder function needs to be generally called before the node is used/submitted.
2972 // - The DockBuilderXXX functions are designed to _eventually_ become a public API, but it is too early to expose it and guarantee stability.
2973 // - Do not hold on ImGuiDockNode* pointers! They may be invalidated by any split/merge/remove operation and every frame.
2974 // - To create a DockSpace() node, make sure to set the ImGuiDockNodeFlags_DockSpace flag when calling DockBuilderAddNode().
2975 // You can create dockspace nodes (attached to a window) _or_ floating nodes (carry its own window) with this API.
2976 // - DockBuilderSplitNode() create 2 child nodes within 1 node. The initial node becomes a parent node.
2977 // - If you intend to split the node immediately after creation using DockBuilderSplitNode(), make sure
2978 // to call DockBuilderSetNodeSize() beforehand. If you don't, the resulting split sizes may not be reliable.
2979 // - Call DockBuilderFinish() after you are done.
2980 IMGUI_API void DockBuilderDockWindow(const char* window_name, ImGuiID node_id);
2981 IMGUI_API ImGuiDockNode*DockBuilderGetNode(ImGuiID node_id);
2982 inline ImGuiDockNode* DockBuilderGetCentralNode(ImGuiID node_id) { ImGuiDockNode* node = DockBuilderGetNode(node_id); if (!node) return NULL; return DockNodeGetRootNode(node)->CentralNode; }
2983 IMGUI_API ImGuiID DockBuilderAddNode(ImGuiID node_id = 0, ImGuiDockNodeFlags flags = 0);
2984 IMGUI_API void DockBuilderRemoveNode(ImGuiID node_id); // Remove node and all its child, undock all windows
2985 IMGUI_API void DockBuilderRemoveNodeDockedWindows(ImGuiID node_id, bool clear_settings_refs = true);
2986 IMGUI_API void DockBuilderRemoveNodeChildNodes(ImGuiID node_id); // Remove all split/hierarchy. All remaining docked windows will be re-docked to the remaining root node (node_id).
2987 IMGUI_API void DockBuilderSetNodePos(ImGuiID node_id, ImVec2 pos);
2988 IMGUI_API void DockBuilderSetNodeSize(ImGuiID node_id, ImVec2 size);
2989 IMGUI_API ImGuiID DockBuilderSplitNode(ImGuiID node_id, ImGuiDir split_dir, float size_ratio_for_node_at_dir, ImGuiID* out_id_at_dir, ImGuiID* out_id_at_opposite_dir); // Create 2 child nodes in this parent node.
2990 IMGUI_API void DockBuilderCopyDockSpace(ImGuiID src_dockspace_id, ImGuiID dst_dockspace_id, ImVector<const char*>* in_window_remap_pairs);

3208 // Refactored focus/nav/tabbing system in 1.82 and 1.84. If you have old/custom copy-and-pasted widgets that used FocusableItemRegister():
3209 // (Old) IMGUI_VERSION_NUM < 18209: using 'ItemAdd(....)' and 'bool tab_focused = FocusableItemRegister(...)'
3210 // (Old) IMGUI_VERSION_NUM >= 18209: using 'ItemAdd(..., ImGuiItemAddFlags_Focusable)' and 'bool tab_focused = (GetItemStatusFlags() & ImGuiItemStatusFlags_Focused) != 0'
3211 // (New) IMGUI_VERSION_NUM >= 18413: using 'ItemAdd(..., ImGuiItemFlags_Inputable)' and 'bool tab_focused = (GetItemStatusFlags() & ImGuiItemStatusFlags_FocusedTabbing) != 0 || g.NavActivateInputId == id' (WIP)
3212 // Widget code are simplified as there's no need to call FocusableItemUnregister() while managing the transition from regular widget to TempInputText()
3213 inline bool FocusableItemRegister(ImGuiWindow* window, ImGuiID id) { IM_ASSERT(0); IM_UNUSED(window); IM_UNUSED(id); return false; } // -> pass ImGuiItemAddFlags_Inputable flag to ItemAdd()
3214 inline void FocusableItemUnregister(ImGuiWindow* window) { IM_ASSERT(0); IM_UNUSED(window); } // -> unnecessary: TempInputText() uses ImGuiInputTextFlags_MergedItem
3215#endif
